text_retweet: posted @withrepost • @frizzkidart today's affirmation art: all survivors are brave. all victims are brave. 💛 those who share their stories of surviving sexual violence/intimate partner violence are brave, but those who may not be able to share their stories or don't want to are also brave. no survivor/victim is cowardly and it's their choice what they want to do with their story. you may also wonder why i chose to include the word "victim." not everyone who experiences sexual violence or intimate partner violence feels like a "survivor." if we want to approach this issue in a "survivor-centric" way, then we can't impose the same strong, recovery, survival narrative on every person impacted by sexual violence/ipv. every survivor/victim is different, navigates their trauma differently, and has different perspectives on justice and healing looks like. in looking at the #metoo movement, i've seen a tendency to want to tell all stories the same way, without realizing that all survivors/victims have different intersections in their identity that a) impacts their likelihood to experience violence and b) changes the way experience justice and reconciliation with trauma. every survivor/victim is worthy of love, respect, and support. every survivor/victim is brave no matter how they choose to cope with their trauma. #art #artist #affirmation #illustration #drawing #draw #healing #heal #justice #metoo #feministart #endrapeculture #selflove #brave #torontoartist #feminist

text:
alla #berlinale firma del protocollo per la parità
il direttore della #berlinale #dieterkosslick firmerà il protocollo per la parità di genere e numerose sono le iniziative in programma al festival, in programma dal 7 al 17 febbraio 2019.
la firma del protocollo, che avverrà il 9 febbraio, nell'ambito del convegno "gender, genre and big budgets", è stata organizzata e promossa dall'associazione women in film and television germany e dal dortmund cologne international women’s film festival in collaborazione con le francesi di 50/50 by 2020. 
la #berlinale è da tempo impegnata nella battaglia della parità, anche da prima che esplodesse il movimento #metoo, come ha ricordato kosslick, sottolineando come quest'anno su 17 film in concorso, 7 siano diretti da registe.

text:
i feel a bit weird writing this because i rarely talk about personal stuff on social media but this is something i want to share this because i will not be the only to feel this way. soon a lot of people will have their reality altered like i did and it’s been fucking rough. i watched one of the first screenings of leaving neverland last saturday. there were only two but it’s going to come out on hbo later this year. 
the simplest way to put it is it fucked me up. like honestly i’ve been physically ill for the past few days just trying to assimilate it. i’m not going to describe the film since everyone will watch it soon but what i will say is i was obsessed with michael jackson in my early teens (anyone who knew me at that age will vouch for the fact that it was ridiculous to the point of insanity), and i always vouched for his innocence, yet after watching this documentary there is now no doubt in my mind that he was a predator. i’m not going to argue with anyone about it right now, because the only thing i can say is “watch the film, then we’ll talk”. anyways as i process this i thought it would be a good opportunity to talk about what i think it means for us in the present, because after all he’s dead and we’re the ones left here feeling shitty. i think there’s many facets to the story, and many questions to ask ourselves and others. the first thing for me as a fan is assimilating that one of the people i admired the most was a very sick person. and then comes the question of how that changes my approach to his art. will i never listen to it because i can’t stop hearing a dark meaning behind every lyric? will i separate the artist and the man, and interpret his art in a way that relates to me?
then i think about the reasons why he did it. was he born sick? did his abusive father make him sick? was he sexually abused as well? was it a combination of being abused as a child, deprived of a childhood because of his stardom and then being given the ability to do it and get away with it through the power we gave him because of his talent? probably. (continued in comment)

text:
gracias por tus "likes", pero sobre todo por portarte bien👼si quieres saber más, lee mis novelas🕵buscad la belleza, es la única protesta que merece la pena en este asqueroso mundo (r. trecet)🍀 si pinchas en este enlace verás cómo me presenta la editorial mito: https://mitoeditorial.blogspot.com/p/autor-invitado.html 👋😹👍🐩💫puedes leer artículos míos en el apartado "colaboradores" de diario alhaurín y en 101 málaga, así como en las revistas culturales guatiní (miami) y mimeógrafo (méxico). también me presentaron en la ventana del arte (la guía más completa sobre exposiciones en españa), revista one stop y en webs y blogs como: munduky y repoelas (ambas españolas) y, en inglés, en art reveal magazine https://go.shr.lc/2u3tk4e 🍹🎻🎶🦄💰💂 📚mis novelas llegan a cualquier lugar 🗺 desde:

verás que están en papel; que puedes leer las primeras páginas, algunas críticas y más... la 1ª también en formato digital. son para mayores🔞you can click the link in my profile. you'll see they are in paper, you can read the first pages, some critics and more... the first one is also for ebook, your computer, etc. they are for adults ✌😘✊ todo lo ocurrido desde que decidí publicar y más en: http://www.margaritabokusumina.blogspot.com 💻

text:
when working with #coaching clients there comes a beautiful moment where the client fully realises his or her own worth, & starts making some seriously self-honouring moves as a result. 🦋 .
.
.
they may literally wake up one morning & decide that -yes - they are going to press charges against the abuser after all. 
or they are going to file for divorce. 
or they’re going back to college. 
or starting that side business they always dreamed about. 
putting plans to move to a new location that nourishes their soul. .
.
.
or maybe it’s a more subtle but equally important breakthrough— such as a decision to block the abuser’s number. 📲 .
.
.
what have some of your major breakthroughs been since realising you’ve been abused by a narcissist?  these are achievements to be proud of, so let’s celebrate your progress. 💫 .
.
.
one of my very first steps in the right direction was way back when i applied for & was awarded a restraining order against the narc. .
.
.
another breakthrough was letting the police know about all the abuse the #narcissist subjected me to. and doing that also means that when the abuser's next victim calls law enforcement (and there is always a next a victim with these individuals) there will already be a record on file to help validate the new victim’s claims.  and the victim after that. .
.
.

the abuser's previous victim before me has said she wishes she'd reported him to police, too.  to document the fact that what he did to her is disgusting & unacceptable -- regardless of whether her complaint led to charges or not.
.
.
.
you?
.
.
.
#narcissisticabuse #breakingthesilence #solidarity #metoo #eachoneteachone #healingfromabuse #narcissisticabuserecoverycoach #lifeafternarc #outofthefog 🌪

text:
here i am, lying awake, not able to stop my racing mind. no matter how long it has been, my heart just can't seem to let go of what i've been through. honestly, i don't believe that my heart will ever truly let go of what happened. 
trauma changes us, it permanently changes us, and for those of us who have lived through it, there really is no such thing as returning to a normal life. once you've been through something truly traumatic, you're forced to live with a new definition of normal. thankfully, this doesn't mean that we can't heal. we can still heal from trauma, not in the sense that all of the pain will be washed away and that we'll be made new, but that we will learn to live again despite all that we've been through. we will learn to live with our scars and do so courageously.
🙏💪💙

text:
這故事不知道從何說起
連要不要說都掙扎好幾個月,

在我國小升國中的時候,因為某些原因必須要看醫生

我記得病房的擺設
我記得一進門那濃郁的藥味
一切的細節除了醫生的臉都歷歷在目
他叫我躺下
他會先儀式性的搓弄我的乳房
再用手指玩弄我的下體 
我嚇壞了 身體動彈不得
只能任由他恣意在我身體裡遊走 時間一切暫停

那時候的我根本不懂保護自己

想要求救
卻連過程都不敢跟大人解釋而作罷隱忍
硬著頭皮繼續看了幾個月 還是一年(我真的想不起來細節)
當然他每次都會重複行為
直到我受不了了拒絕再見到他才結束
這件事也就這樣被我封塵 大腦好似啟動自我保護裝置屏蔽了這段記憶 -

故事回到去年
有一陣子心情不是很好,晚上我去他家聊天 
我想說他最近同病相憐 
我們可以一起吐吐苦水
he is my friend, nothing more. 
很久沒見,聊了一晚,說了很多屁話
看他醉了 時間也差不多

我說我該回家了,他把我按在床上
我說不要,他強吻了我,
我在哭,他卻在脫褲子,

掙扎一陣子沒有用後
我開始配合他
一心這樣可以早點結束這場鬧劇
一方面又對自己的回應感到羞恥 阿 我的身體出賣我的意願
天啊 我好難過 如果是我喜歡的對象才不會用這種方式親我對我 -

我賞了他幾巴掌(自以為可以討回一點主導權)
反正又不是沒有交過炮友 這次又有什麼不同 ?
我就這樣騙自己跟身邊的人
逃避問題

但去年下半年整個人渾渾噩噩
背負著來自各方的負面情緒
結果爆炸 發生車禍情緒瓦解

一個人離開了家 總有很多夜晚特別脆弱
花了很久時間才開始吐露
好在身邊的人的鼓勵
我漸漸意識到我必須對自己坦白 沒錯就是發生了這樣的事情
跟身邊親近的人聊了很多
我才慢慢把破碎的自己一點點拼回來

有時候情緒很好,有時很down
像鐘擺來回 
快樂逐漸比難過多-

很謝謝身邊幾位天使,不厭其煩地聽我抱怨,
有時候看到他們小心翼翼 或是比我更生氣
又覺得他們好可愛,我還是被疼愛

日子大多回歸平靜,但偶爾又來幾個夜晚理智斷線
憂鬱襲來 輾轉難眠
難過夾雜生氣
為什麼是我要受這些情緒
為什麼是我覺得羞恥
為什麼是我要承擔後果

一度覺得男人特別噁
只要自己爽,可以完全不在乎對方想法, 他可以一邊珍惜他所愛的對象,一邊傷害他人 任由我在旁邊腐爛
我反覆地陷入自我價值的質疑

他可能會因為我當下的反應 一輩子不知道我受傷
我把秘密公開出來 不知道對不對
但我想要正視這件事情
我也不確定現在的我夠不夠堅強面對公開後的回應
- 
這封信是寫給有相同經驗的妳/你
你不是一個人
不要覺得是你做錯事
如果你想要找個窗口聊聊 歡迎私訊我 
我願意當你的避風港
一個safe place to talk 
我們雖然不能改變過去,但可以讓環境變得更有愛

如果你是想要安慰我 或是了解當下的6個w
那我謝謝你的好意,我還沒準備好要反覆咀嚼

i’m sick of being a victim, i’m strong as fuck, i’m a survivor-

第一次發生這樣事情的時候
我氣我自己不懂保護自己
第二次我不想就這樣放任 我想要面對我自己的心魔
我要拿回故事的主導權
我想要對11歲徬徨的我勇敢一回

經過這段經驗 更感激身邊所有的kindness
珍視身邊的親友
如此純粹的愛 真的很難得 謝謝你們 
所以我也想要把我所受到的力量 分享給需要的你
i’ll be here with you :)
#metoo

stop_filter_tweet: 這故事不知道從何說起 連要不要說都掙扎好幾個月 , 在我國小升國中的時候 , 因為某些原因必須要看醫生 我記得病房的擺設 我記得一進門那濃郁的藥味 一切的細節除了醫生的臉都歷歷在目 他叫我躺下 他會先儀式性的搓弄我的乳房 再用手指玩弄我的下體 我嚇壞了 身體動彈不得 只能任由他恣意在我身體裡遊走 時間一切暫停 那時候的我根本不懂保護自己 想要求救 卻連過程都不敢跟大人解釋而作罷隱忍 硬著頭皮繼續看了幾個月 還是一年 ( 我真的想不起來細節 ) 當然他每次都會重複行為 直到我受不了了拒絕再見到他才結束 這件事也就這樣被我封塵 大腦好似啟動自我保護裝置屏蔽了這段記憶 - 故事回到去年 有一陣子心情不是很好 , 晚上我去他家聊天 我想說他最近同病相憐 我們可以一起吐吐苦水 friend , nothing . 很久沒見 , 聊了一晚 , 說了很多屁話 看他醉了 時間也差不多 我說我該回家了 , 他把我按在床上 我說不要 , 他強吻了我 , 我在哭 , 他卻在脫褲子 , 掙扎一陣子沒有用後 我開始配合他 一心這樣可以早點結束這場鬧劇 一方面又對自己的回應感到羞恥 阿 我的身體出賣我的意願 天啊 我好難過 如果是我喜歡的對象才不會用這種方式親我對我 - 我賞了他幾巴掌 ( 自以為可以討回一點主導權 ) 反正又不是沒有交過炮友 這次又有什麼不同 ? 我就這樣騙自己跟身邊的人 逃避問題 但去年下半年整個人渾渾噩噩 背負著來自各方的負面情緒 結果爆炸 發生車禍情緒瓦解 一個人離開了家 總有很多夜晚特別脆弱 花了很久時間才開始吐露 好在身邊的人的鼓勵 我漸漸意識到我必須對自己坦白 沒錯就是發生了這樣的事情 跟身邊親近的人聊了很多 我才慢慢把破碎的自己一點點拼回來 有時候情緒很好 , 有時很down 像鐘擺來回 快樂逐漸比難過多- 很謝謝身邊幾位天使 , 不厭其煩地聽我抱怨 , 有時候看到他們小心翼翼 或是比我更生氣 又覺得他們好可愛 , 我還是被疼愛 日子大多回歸平靜 , 但偶爾又來幾個夜晚理智斷線 憂鬱襲來 輾轉難眠 難過夾雜生氣 為什麼是我要受這些情緒 為什麼是我覺得羞恥 為什麼是我要承擔後果 一度覺得男人特別噁 只要自己爽 , 可以完全不在乎對方想法 , 他可以一邊珍惜他所愛的對象 , 一邊傷害他人 任由我在旁邊腐爛 我反覆地陷入自我價值的質疑 他可能會因為我當下的反應 一輩子不知道我受傷 我把秘密公開出來 不知道對不對 但我想要正視這件事情 我也不確定現在的我夠不夠堅強面對公開後的回應 - 這封信是寫給有相同經驗的妳/你 你不是一個人 不要覺得是你做錯事 如果你想要找個窗口聊聊 歡迎私訊我 我願意當你的避風港 一個safe place talk 我們雖然不能改變過去 , 但可以讓環境變得更有愛 如果你是想要安慰我 或是了解當下的6個w 那我謝謝你的好意 , 我還沒準備好要反覆咀嚼 ’ sick victim , ’ strong fuck , ’ survivor- 第一次發生這樣事情的時候 我氣我自己不懂保護自己 第二次我不想就這樣放任 我想要面對我自己的心魔 我要拿回故事的主導權 我想要對11歲徬徨的我勇敢一回 經過這段經驗 更感激身邊所有的kindness 珍視身邊的親友 如此純粹的愛 真的很難得 謝謝你們 所以我也想要把我所受到的力量 分享給需要的你 ’ : )

text:
we have heard it a million times. be who you want to be. but the lessons we are often taught when we look to others are more like “be who you want to be as long as it makes me comfortable” “be who you want to be as long as it stays within how you have defined yourself in the past”
“be who you want to be as long as you do not rock the boat”
“be who you want to be as long as you are private about it” 
effffffff no. 
who you are itching to embody...do it without shame. without fear. without apology. because you can. and because you are meant to show others the way. 
life is short. live it on your terms, my friend.

gracias por tus "likes", pero sobre todo por portarte bien👼si quieres saber más, lee mis novelas🕵buscad la belleza, es la única protesta que merece la pena en este asqueroso mundo (r. trecet)🍀 si pinchas en este enlace verás cómo me presenta la editorial mito: https://mitoeditorial.blogspot.com/p/autor-invitado.html 👋😹👍🐩💫puedes leer artículos míos en el apartado "colaboradores" de diario alhaurín y en 101 málaga, así como en las revistas culturales guatiní (miami) y mimeógrafo (méxico). también me presentaron en la ventana del arte (la guía más completa sobre exposiciones en españa), revista one stop y en webs y blogs como: munduky y repoelas (ambas españolas) y, en inglés, en art reveal magazine https://go.shr.lc/2u3tk4e 🍹🎻🎶🦄💰💂 📚mis novelas llegan a cualquier lugar 🗺 desde: 
my novels arrive everywhere from

http://www.bubok.es/autores/bokusu
pincha el enlace en mi perfil.

verás que están en papel; que puedes leer las primeras páginas, algunas críticas y más... la 1ª también en formato digital. son para mayores🔞you can click the link in my profile. you'll see they are in paper, you can read the first pages, some critics and more... the first one is also for ebook, your computer, etc. they are for adults✌😘✊ todo lo ocurrido desde que decidí publicar y más en: http://www.margaritabokusumina.blogspot.com 💻puedes seguirme además en youtube, fb (2 perfiles, uno más usado que el otro, y una página de autora), en twitter y soundcloud 🎤(otros 2 perfiles, uno de ellos con más de 30 grabaciones en español, inglés y francés macarrónico)📲 gitano si me kisieras/okuparía en graná/la mejor kueva ke hubiera💃

text:
“i’m tired of bein’ the victim of hate”
—————————————————
—————————————————
michael jackson’s name is once again being dragged through the mud with claims of child abuse although there’s fbi files, tapes proving extortion, evidence completely in his favor, multiple witness testimonies, court documents, and a criminal trial with a not guilty verdict except this time he’s not here to defend himself these claims of sexual abuse by two men who came out with their claims after one was denied a job with michaels estate and multiple other deals he filed a 1.3 billion dollar civil suit because of his financial ruin in 2012 the suit was dismissed and michaels estate demands legal fees to be paid. the two men played a part in making a documentary titled ‘leaving neverland’ that premiered at sundance this year the documentary used shock factor techniques to persuade the audience into believing mj was some sick creep who preyed on and enjoyed the company of young boys. those who know of these allegations and have looked into the inconsistency of them know that it is far from the truth michael jackson was the complete opposite he was a loving and giving human being. wade robson, the leading man of this documentary and the allegations was the first person called to testify in michaels defense in 2005 wade was an adult at the time swearing michael never harmed him. wade was never contacted to testify in michaels defense he offered to and michael allowed it, so to think michael ever sexually abused him or any child is absurd if michael truly abused him would he had trusted him to be his first witness on the stand that could set the entire tone for his criminal trial? the simple answer to that is no. wade robson is a lying extortionist using michael jackson’s name to gain fame and money and the media is allowing him to do so this man is making a mockery of the #metoo movement and it’s true victims. it’s time the media tell the truth and expose these men for the liars they are. •
•
•
•
•
•
•
•
• #michaeljackson #mjj #mj #kingofpop #blackpride #blacklivesmatter #blm #leavingneverland #blackpower #blackexcellence

text:
ブレスレットのパーツ作りつつ考えてる。

某テレビ局が #スクールセクハラ なんて軽々しい造語使って避難浴びてたけど。

教師や親などといった「強い立場」を悪用した性暴力やる奴ってね。
相手に薬飲ませてレイプするレイプ犯と大差ない卑劣だと私は思ってる。

gracias por tus "likes", pero sobre todo por portarte bien👼si quieres saber más, lee mis novelas🕵buscad la belleza, es la única protesta que merece la pena en este asqueroso mundo (r. trecet)🍀 si pinchas en este enlace verás cómo me presenta la editorial mito: https://mitoeditorial.blogspot.com/p/autor-invitado.html 👋😹👍🐩💫puedes leer artículos míos en el apartado "colaboradores" de diario alhaurín y en 101 málaga, así como en las revistas culturales guatiní (miami) y mimeógrafo (méxico). también me presentaron en la ventana del arte (la guía más completa sobre exposiciones en españa), revista one stop y en webs y blogs como: munduky y repoelas (ambas españolas) y, en inglés, en art reveal magazine https://go.shr.lc/2u3tk4e 🍹🎻🎶🦄💰💂 📚mis novelas llegan a cualquier lugar 🗺 desde: 
my novels arrive everywhere from

http://www.bubok.es/autores/bokusu
pincha el enlace en mi perfil.

verás que están en papel; que puedes leer las primeras páginas, algunas críticas y más... la 1ª también en formato digital. son para mayores🔞you can click the link in my profile. you'll see they are in paper, you can read the first pages, some critics and more... the first one is also for ebook, your computer, etc. they are for adults✌😘✊ todo lo ocurrido desde que decidí publicar y más en: http://www.margaritabokusumina.blogspot.com 💻puedes seguirme además en youtube, fb (2 perfiles, uno más usado que el otro, y una página de autora), en twitter y soundcloud 🎤(otros 2 perfiles, uno de ellos con más de 30 grabaciones en español, inglés y francés macarrónico)📲 gitano si me kisieras/okuparía en graná/la mejor kueva ke hubiera💃

text:
let's get personal for a second..
i have a fair share of people in my life that doubt my dreams. •"it's not going anywhere." •"it’s inconsistent, you can't pay your bills like that." • "do you really think you'll be on @antmvh1 in front of @tyrabanks ?!” what most people aren't aware of is that modeling has absolutely nothing to do with fame and everything to do with self confidence and growth. 
i was first introduced to modeling roughly around the age of 6 by a family friend. or, atleast, what i was told was modeling. 
quickly summarized, i was being used for child pornography. forever scarring me in every way throughout not only childhood, but adulthood as well. i went through life  untrustworthy of men, i flinched when someone unexpectedly bumped into me or went in for a hug. i hated taking pictures or being near a camera. i hated being sexualized in any way. 
at 21, i decided i would no longer let such an evil, sadistic, perverted man determine my self confidence, self love or femininity. so i joined a group online for models and began my search towards liberation. that’s where i met @sammiechic , an amazing hmua and friend, who has without a doubt held my hand through every detail of every shoot.  don’t get me wrong..a couple years later i still get nervous on set, i still feel a little awkward trying to be sexy, i still flinch when people get too close to me, i’m very selective with who i’ll shoot with, sometimes it’s hard for me to take a genuine compliment and i’m much harder on myself than anyone else has been or ever will be. but the point is, i am healing. 
no, i don't do this to earn fame or money. i do this for myself. making art has aided in my journey towards healing. it's something i never thought i'd be capable of applying myself to, but here i am. because i deserve to feel safe, worthy and beautiful. so do you.

text: if i had to classify my politics i would have to say i identify most with "fourth-wave feminism". fourth-wave feminism began around 2012 and is associated with the belief that all humans are equal. it heavily focuses on intersectionality, pushig for greater empowermentof traditionally marginalized groups in society, including women and girls.  fourth-wave feminists advocate for greater representation of these groups in politics and business, and argue that we would have a more equitable society when we incorporate the perspectives of all citizens. whereas earlier feminists fought for and earned women greater liberation, individualism, and social mobility, the new wave furthers the agenda by calling for justice against assault and harassment, equal pay for equal work, and the freedom to make individual choices over own bodies.  fourth-wave feminists collaborate and mobilize, often using modern technologies, to publicly speak against abusers of power and to provide opportunities for girls and women to be properly recognized and compensated for who they are and what they offer. in addition to advocating for women's issues, feminists point out that boys and men should have greater opportunities to be engaged parents to their children, to express their emotions and feelings freely, and to present themselves and their individualities in the ways they wish.

| metoo fashion | ogilvy sao paolo has created a touch-sensitive dress that tracks how often, and with what degree of intensity, women in brazil were groped on a night out at clubs. the sensor information was relayed to a visual system, where researchers could track harassment in real time.⁣
⁣
the goal of the “dress for respect” campaign was to elevate the issue to men, who had been skeptical during preliminary interviews that unwanted groping was a problem for women.⁣
⁣
with the #metoo and #timesup initiatives showing their staying power into 2019, more and more brands are increasingly finding their voices and sources of inspiration within politicized spaces.⁣
⁣

text: hi humans. i’m doing a project inspired by the me too movement which incorporates photos that i’ve taken into a drawing. the me too movement fights sexual assault and harassment, so for this project i am looking for individuals who are survivors of sexual assault or have been impacted by the movement personally to model for some photos that will be incorporated into the piece. (sexual harassment/ sexual assault has many forms and is not limited to any one gender, age, race or sexuality) the portraits will be cropped and disjointed in a way that will protect your identity and your name will not be associated with the piece unless you want it to be. if you are interested please dm me and we can set up a time and place to collab!! i’m really excited and think that with your help we can accomplish a piece that pulls some weight. #metoo #timesup

name: Daring to Dad
pre_proc_tweet:
this is where i’m currently at in my approach to masculinity. i don’t see the problem as ceain behaviors (although there a definitely some that are dangerous), but it’s the enforcement of those behaviors on others for whom that approach might not work for. the whole “you’re not a man if...” statement automatically raises a flag for me. if my wife’s makes more money than me, can i still be a man? yes. if i don’t like to shoot guns or hunt, am i a man? yes. if i love another man, am i still a man? yes. if i enjoy theater more than spos, am i still a man? yes. masculinity can have so many beautiful expressions. the issue is the small man box that has been built to contain a few characteristics that are then enforced on everyone else. for more on the man box, see: .
.
 
 
 
 ....and those are just a few.
.
.
.

text:
meet 2019 rise fellow: aliza amar
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
aliza amar was 21-years-old when her life changed forever. she was raped during a job interview. her assailant recorded the assault and distributed the footage as pornography. amar rose from the fog of despair and shame to inspire countless survivors to make their voices heard and address the growing epidemic of rape, sexual assault, and human trafficking. as a leader in the san diego #metoo movement and the founder of breaking the silence together, a san diego-based nonprofit advocating to bring change in the violence against women, she is helping others rise just like she did. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
as a changemaker, aliza works to empower people towards tangible social change. her story is a reminder that we all have the strength within us to become leaders and be the source of change. currently, she’s working at the las colinas women’s jail, and a girl rehab facility, inspiring women to turn their life into personal victory. she believes within each woman lies a leader who waits to be born. her biggest aspiration is opening open heart marketplace, a retail store that will be operated by survivors of human sex trafficking and prostitution. it gives survivors the opportunity to support their family by earning their living with power and dignity, and honor. aliza holds a bs in human services and a project management certificate. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text:
stephanie beatriz on directing ‘brooklyn nine-nine’s’ #metoo episode – variety
#
“brooklyn nine-nine” made its move from fox to nbc this month, marking the sixth season stephanie beatriz is portraying the gruff but lovable det. rosa diaz. it is her longest-running role, and it may just be the one most close to her, as she personally inspired rosa’s coming out storyline on the show last season. but beatriz is not a one-character wonder, also grabbing attention for her portrayal of gloria’s sister on “modern family,” her vocal performances in the animated “danger & eggs” and “bojack horseman,” and starring in and exec producing indie feature “the light of the moon” in 2017. what keeps “brooklyn nine-nine” fresh for you, this far in and knowing rosa inside and out? what struck me when you just said that is “oh no, i don’t!” this woman is someone who keeps so many secrets, and i think she’s one of those women that keeps secrets from herself, really. and what’s been exciting about the development of the character over the course of now six seasons is that the writers continue to surprise me — especially in the way that they’re able to find a really funny balance between who rosa wants to be in the…

image description: -
[first slide]
“tips for dating someone with anxiety” [second slide]
this is a tumblr post by ‘mylifelivingwithanxiety’ saying: - reassure them constantly. (this may be annoying but they will be thankful.)
- keep them in the loop of your life. (this means share plans with them. it will keep them at ease.)
- text them when you are on your way, or when you get home. (this may seem obnoxious but their brain will thank you.)
- hugs. (after anxious days something as little as a hug can make things better.)
- triggers. identify them. (this one will be hard. once you figure out what makes them anxious it will help you to make them feel safe.)
- no surprises unless you know it will make them happy. (surprises can be hard to handle for anxious people. it will depend on their anxiety level.)
- change is hard. (try to limit major changes in your relationship if possible. things will change but he ready to help your partner get through it.)
- be there. just be there. (as complex as an anxiety disorder can get, the best thing you can do is to be there and let them know you are.) end image description.

text:
for our fifth issue, overachiever magazine explores the metoo movement’s impact on the asian community. in a traditionally patriarchal, conservative society, a movement that centers around female empowerment, open dialogue about sexual assault, and holding men accountable was sure to make waves. in this issue, our talented contributors share their own metoo stories, show how our culture excuses sexual assault and victim blames, and even show the side we willfully ignore of a prominent historical figure.
i want to thank every woman who shared her story. it takes a lot of courage to give even an opinion on the topic in our community. you are paving the way for a more open, honest discussion and culture.
as always, thank you to the team at overachiever magazine. you are the most brilliant and supportive people.
keep sharing your stories. keep giving your opinions. keep reading, sharing, and supporting asian women.

rehana paul, editor
.
.
.
.

text: jean wyllys has clashed with bolsonaro in the chamber of deputies on many occasions. bolsonaro himself is a proud homophobe, supporter of brazil’s military dictatorship, and a rampant sexist. attacks on lgbt people in brazil is amongst the highest rates in the world, and the election of this bigot has been taken as a normalisation of this sort of behaviour. this is especially notable, following the murder of wyllys’ close friend, feminist activist marielle franco, earlier this year. with bolsonaro encouraging this exile of wyllys, it is a clear indication of the horrendous prospects for brazil’s minorities under this man. if you don’t believe bolsonaro’s record, search up some of his quotes. the man’s a proud bigot. #lulalivre

text:
"stop slut shaming"
سَلٹ شیمینگ بند کرو.
swipe left and read each statement. 
some days back, one of my friend's sister asked me,
'what is slut api?'
i was bewildered.
i replied, 'why do you want to know, have you heard someone saying this term'.
according to her, she had heard one of her male cousin calling slut to a classmate. and upon inquiring from him about why he is calling her slut, he said that she has a loose character and most of the class's boys are her friend. 
i asked quietly, 'doesn't he also have female friends?'
she laughed on this.
and said, 'he has many girlfriends'.
.
.
.
this was the point i could no longer take in years of slut shaming, name calling and blame games.
hence, here is what i think about calling women with dishonorable names. 
do read my next post about it too. 
#astaloot

text:
hola, @lorena710 de este lado👋🏾
this month our topic was into the future. that can mean many things for many, for me it has meant justice. the stories coming forward from women made against  men from all facets of the public eye, and the way its been received has been different from the past. from r. kelly to brett kavanaugh, many of these men might not be getting some legal punishment for sexual misconduct against women but they are getting penalized in other ways. 
in the past, when one heard allegations similar to these not much was done to the perpetrators due to their standing in the public eye. recently things have gone differently thanks to both the time's up and #metoo movements. 
to me, the future is seeing how our culture is finally trying to protect women who's stories in the past have gone ignored✊🏾
. . . 
hola, @lorena710 de este lado 👋🏾
este mes nuestro tema fue hacia el futuro. eso se significa muchas cosas para muchos, pero para mi se significa la justicia. las historias que hemos escuchados de mujeres contra hombres de todas las facetas del ojo público, y  la manera que se recibio ha sido diferente del pasado. de r. el kelly a brett kavanaugh, muchos de estos hombres no cojieron castigo legal por la mala conducta sexual contra mujeres sino que están siendo penalizados de otras maneras. en el pasado, cuando uno escuchaba alegaciones similares a éstas nadie hacia nada a los perpretadores debido a su posicion con el público. las cosas han ido cambiando recientemente diferentemente gracias a time's up y al movimiento de #metoo. 
el futuro es como nuestra cultura esta finalmente tratando de proteger a mujeres que su historias en el pasado fueron ignoradas✊🏾
📸 @carlitaz_way

text:
grandma jean and i shared a lot of goofy belly laughing moments on the sweet little island of skopelos, greece…

nine years ago i wanted nothing more than a fresh start. my legal obligations were complete and i felt as if i was the smallest person on the planet. i finished my bachelor’s degree and supported the process of getting a serial predator in prison. i was exhausted and unsure what to do next. 
grandma jean needed a care provider and i knew with every part of my being i was the woman for the job. little did i know she would care for me far more than i would ever care for her.

never did i disclose to her why i moved to her little greek island. yet she clearly knew and became my greatest teacher and closest friend.

she taught me to say, “i’ll do whatever i damn well please.” with no apologies to follow or the need to explain.

she taught me how to belly laugh at the most inappropriate but amazing times.

she taught me that a little confidence goes along way.

she taught me the true meaning of a meaningful relationship. with no expectations and no hidden agenda.

this #tbt is for you grandma jean. thank you loving me even though i watered down your oversized bottle of white wine. 🙊🍷😂 #beher #makeadifference
#metoo
#ibelievesurvivors
#istandwithsurvivors #bellylaugh

text:
are you a people pleaser? are you tortured by the idea that someone might not like you? i admit, i can struggle with this too. but it's important to recognize that the stress & anxiety that can come from trying to keep up with everyone's opinion of you is not only exhausting, it's unhealthy both emotionally & physically.

for some people, they can’t help to want everyone around them to like them. sometimes, at the sacrifice of their own wants, needs & desires.

people pleasing can look an awful lot like admirably generous or helpful behavior. but there’s a difference: while true generosity comes from healthy self-regard & a genuine happiness from shared enjoyment, people pleasing comes from a place of lowered self-regard & a need for others’ approval.

so, decide to block out all the noise, let it go & focus on being a someone that you feel good about. 💗 #loveyourself #selfcare

text:
every thought is a wish and a prayer •
the election of 45 brought on a rage and sadness i didn’t expect. i never thought of myself as an angry person. i got stuck in a cycle of depression. 
in the past two years we’ve seen hate crimes rise, we’ve seen white terrorists plastered all over the media doing their thing, the #metoo campaign and so many other hateful events. it’s triggered so many emotions that i have still not truly dealt with. 
my heart was drowning. 
i just started therapy for the first time and i’m dealing with raw emotions and old wounds reopening. it feels good to release. as i release i’m noticing and learning new things about myself. •
1) being a woman of color in america and really all over the fucking world is scary. i need support.
2) it’s ok to be angry. i need an outlet. 
3) we are affected by not just our immediate environment but also by our society. 
3) ptsd from all this bullshit is real •
in the meantime, i’m focusing on all the good in my life. i have so much to be thankful for. 
self preservation: i’m detoxing from the media. i’m moving my body again. meditation is calming my thoughts. my spiritual practice is softening my edges. 
slowly dropping back into my body. it feels good. i feel more present. •
more thoughts on therapy to come
(art by @abbiepaulhus)
.
.
.
#prayers #woc #poc #latinx #intersectionalfeminism #witchesofinstagram

text: i literally cannot believe how much i’m reading in 2019 lmao but i just finished putney by sofka zinovieff. i read a review for this book that called it “lolita for the #metoo era” and even though that sentence makes me cringe, it’s definitely the best way to describe it. this story follows daphne, now in her 40s, as she struggles to come to terms with a relationship she had with an older man when she was a teenager. it switches off from her pov, to her abuser’s, to her best friend’s. it was sooo good even though it felt hard to read sometimes. 8/10!

text:
during meditation i heard spirit speak "you will be given fifth dimensional sight" and i was shown an angelic realm.

the realm i was seeing served humanity with compassion, these angels surrounded our planet and were crying. i was filled with an emotion of deep deep love, it felt like the type of love a mother would feel for her child when her child is suffering, suffering inside themselves from something that is causing great anguish. it was the type of love that resonated as such a strong desire for her child to "know" they are more, to "know" they do not need to suffer, to "know all things are in perfect order" and to trust their inner voice.

when i have these visions (downloads) they are very difficult to describe with words, the emotion attached to the vision is essentially indescribable. the vision (for those who do not or have not opened themselves up to this gift) are very fast and last from our 3 dimensional "time" perspective as a few seconds however, the vision itself is greatly detailed and timeless and the amount of information i'm translating seems impossible to have been received in 1 or 2 seconds. 
the angels are weeping tears of sadness for those who are suffering anguish. they feel each of our individual suffering not because we are "lost" but in the same manor as that of a mother who desires for her child to live a life filled with joy and love and to know and trust their inner power.

when i felt and saw the sadness i could feel and see how deeply these angelic beings love us, i could feel their desire for humanity to stop punishing themselves and i could feel their understanding and acceptance of each persons choices to learn and grow within their own experience without judgement, they love us unconditionally. ❤  message from the angels.

children, we are all gods children and we are loved deeply. we suffer within your suffering and we do this to ease your individual burdens as you live your lives and express yourselves. each of you are a very special gift and you come from and will all return to your light. suffer not with that which was and is created by the flesh and know peace will follow.
name: Spirit Connection

i am a heterosexual cisgender woman, and i constantly grapple with how i can fight for gender inclusivity in this movement without taking up space that should be highlighting voices in the queer community. what i am always committed to though, is bringing up the need for gender inclusivity in all aspects of this #menstrualmovement especially as we gain more visibility, and recognizing the incredible work of activists like @theperiodprince who started #bleedingwhiletrans 👊🏽 tips for how to be a better ally? comment below!
.
pc: jin lee of @shethinx

text:
unleashed.
untamed.
unapologetic.
in today’s world, specially with social media you constantly hear what you should or shouldn’t be doing.
no matter what you hear, do what the fuck sits right with you and makes you happy. i don’t need to go on and say “so long as you don’t hurt yourself or others..” because i’m assuming we all have common sense. 
yesterday me and @synergysoul_ talked about this shit, everybody wants to box others or themselves into labels everybody is on here with their big internet balls trying to tell the world what to do and point fingers at what others are doing “wrong” or talk shit about people who believe in different things than them. the mothafuckin’ beauty of humanity is diversity. i talked about how i filter my words a lot to the point where sometimes i can’t even talk cause i never wanna make someone feel bad about themselves not because i care what anybody thinks about me. i live my truth. when i put my phone down, in the real fucking world i live my mothafuckin’ truth no matter where the fuck i’m at. i fucking love my life and i love the beauty i see in everything, i love knowing i can create whatever the fuck i want. i’m not here to get anyone’s approval and if i don’t hold back with my mom and daughters and i tell them straight up what the fuck is up i don’t need to be babying no bitches i don’t even know.
my word for this year is unbothered.
the world could be set on fire and i’m good. you know what the problem is? everybody wants to change other’s perspectives instead of working on their shit. you know why a lot of people focus on the terror? cause that’s what the fuck they feel inside. they’re afraid of everything including their own mothafuckin’ power and so they try to strip others from theirs, that way they feel like they have a chance, wrong bitch, a lion doesn’t worry, get anxiety or feel guilty for his nature, a lion doesn’t need to be reminded he’s a fucking lion a lion simply is the mothafuckin’ king of the jungle and any bitch that questions that ends up on its teeth. everybody gets bothered by anything cause yall bitches rather cry and point fingers than take control of your shit and be a fucking goddess.

text:
👶 mother nature is one amazing thing!

i find the whole fact we are able to make babies in these bodies of ours simply incredible.

our bodies are capable of building a whole human being cell by cell. we can give a baby all the nutrients they need for 9months without them consuming a drop of water or eating a mouthful of food themselves.

and then, when they finally enter the world our bodies are already prepared to feed them again, completely naturally. it’s incredible.

so for every person who frowns upon a woman breast feeding in public, i think you need to check on your opinions and why they are there. there’s little i could say is a more natural process in our world now.

text: hearing things that people don’t like about us can be hard to take, but how else can we learn? i suggest that we all take in criticism as ‘feedback’ instead of condemnation. we can hear it, decide whether or not we agree with it, and then choose if we want to take any action to make changes in our lives. that way, we can turn other people’s opinions into a gift instead of a curse. and if we truly believe they are wrong, we can let it go!

text:
hoy recomendamos!
en este texto, fruto de más de cuarenta años dedicados a la formación de actores, uta hagen define los objetivos que debe perseguir un actor y proporciona las técnicas específicas para lograrlos. así, plantea ahondar en los sentidos físicos y en la propia psicología para ofrecer una buena interpretación, y propone ejercicios que permiten recrear emociones auténticas en escena.

gran conocedora de las dificultades con que se enfrenta un actor al dar vida a un personaje, ofrece también soluciones a dificultades concretas como la forma de recrear el aire libre en la escena, encontrar una ocupación mientras se espera en el escenario, hablar con el público, aprender a usar la imaginación histórica y ser capaz de interpretar personajes de época con auténtica convicción. en definitiva, uta hagen ofrece un sinnúmero de ayudas prácticas que han hecho de ella una de las pedagogas más influyentes de estados unidos, con alumnos tan destacados como geraldine page y jack lemmon, y de un reto para el actor un bestséller en lo que a aprendizaje teatral se refiere.
@albaeditorial
.
.
.
. .

gran conocedora de las dificultades con que se enfrenta un actor al dar vida a un personaje, ofrece también soluciones a dificultades concretas como la forma de recrear el aire libre en la escena, encontrar una ocupación mientras se espera en el escenario, hablar con el público, aprender a usar la imaginación histórica y ser capaz de interpretar personajes de época con auténtica convicción. en definitiva, uta hagen ofrece un sinnúmero de ayudas prácticas que han hecho de ella una de las pedagogas más influyentes de estados unidos, con alumnos tan destacados como geraldine page y jack lemmon, y de un reto para el actor un bestséller en lo que a aprendizaje teatral se refiere.

text:
i came to gems four years ago. at 20, i was a young mother and wanted to do the best by my son. however, i found myself with very few choices and close to no support. i fell into “the life” as a way to make ends meet for myself and my son. it wasn’t the quick solution that i thought it might be, and there were times that i was even homeless. eventually, i received help and learned about the work that gems does. i’ll always remember my first day at the center. i was scared and nervous, but the staff was very welcoming – and i felt like going there was a good decision. within time, it felt like home. i received consistent case management at gems and regularly attended groups, which was one of the first steps to obtaining my financial independence. gems helped me strengthen my leadership skills as i became a mentor for the sista mentoring project and a participant in ei. within one year, i successfully completed my hha certification. since then, i have moved out of new york with my son, am working full-time as an hha and am looking forward to enrolling in college. #gemsgirls .

text:
sending love to black women and people w/ mental illness, w/ disabilities who live through hell most people won't, but whose experiences are invalidated, who are expected to be superhuman but your needs are unseen, and labeled defective when you need a break.

i know. i know that racism makes sexism look like love. mental health and disability discrimination makes racism look like respect. that rape makes the rest doable. 
i was sexually assaulted for over a decade as a child. my siblings, my friends were not. growing up i slept w/ a dresser barricading my door or stayed awake all night. i still have ptsd and night terrors. my siblings, my friends do not. 
but to hear them, they had harder lives.
my brothers claim more disadvantage because i was young when we left chicago. but every year growing up i went back, alone, for months to my unsafe chicago neighborhood because it was safer for me than wny. people can be animals who’ll try to use & abuse people like me for our looks, title, position, etc. my siblings don't need to worry about that. 
but they and white friends (in the white racist community i was raised in) claim less privilege because i was scouted to play college ball, i got into the best colleges. i had to fight more unfair systems & prejudices than the ones they claim handicapped them.
and when i couldn't get a good job in an insular, parochial and racist upstate ny legal community i opened my own law firm. by the time i closed it i was winning legal awards & being asking to run for judge.
i navigated, alone, through 80 hour weeks & the hyper stress of work where one mistake has dire consequences because when i became a lawyer i became the first professional in my orbit. but karen didn't change the office toner so their lives are harder. colleagues who can't have my resume, & who benefit from disability & mental health discrimination i'm harmed by, call me a flame out when i need a break. it's sad that my story is typical of black woman & people with disabilities. sharing it so anyone who thinks they're going it alone knows that they aren't. 
#love #blackqueen #blackwomenmatter #ptsd #ptsdawareness #disability #metoo

text:
<<< #men’swork >>> over the past couple years-especially since the #metoo #movement began to prevail- there has been a massive uprising in #women standing in their #power. recently, i have noticed a great deal of men stepping up to “do the work” of personal and collective healing, #transformation and activation of the masculine. 
when we first decided to host the elemental retreat - i was apprehensive. mostly because i didn’t think i was “man enough”. my entire life- my relationship with men went something like - sexual abuse from a coach, followed by a lack of emotional support from all men, and a sad excuse for positive male role models in my particular chosen friend groups.. thank god for my mom to bake some common sense and value into me.. but when we decided to hit “go” on the #elemental evolved masculine immersion #retreat- it was a massive initiation for me. i really had to step up into my power as a man. organize. #empower. and actually believe it it! a few of the profound shift that happened along the way:

1. learned not to give a #fuck about what people think about me. i am a man. i have #emotions, #desires, needs, strengths, weaknesses, and they are all perfect. so often - as a man - i have found myself feeling as if i need to be strong all the time- but now i see so much beauty, even in the pain, #trauma, and #triumph of my brothers.

2. i gained an entirely new perception on the importance of values like honor (sacred union of the masculine and feminine), integrity (to myself and the other), kindness, and service (how are you showing up for your brothers)? these all deepened in my heart and mind this week as i began to revise my core values, as a man.

3. radical transparency- showing up to every situation with child- like curiosity, yet boldly speaking truth- even if it has the potential to scare someone away... essentially- in regards to the feminine- i aim to be able to speak my truth in order to no the #righteously aligned tribe will survive. 
4. #sacredsexuality- overall, a theme i see in my own life and through this retreat is the divine reunion of the sacred #masculine and #feminine. more on this soon.. my mind and heart are wide open

when we first decided to host the elemental retreat - i was apprehensive. mostly because i didn’t think i was “man enough”. my entire life- my relationship with men went something like - sexual abuse from a coach, followed by a lack of emotional support from all men, and a sad excuse for positive male role models in my particular chosen friend groups.. thank god for my mom to bake some common sense and value into me.. but when we decided to hit “go” on the #elemental evolved masculine immersion #retreat- it was a massive initiation for me. i really had to step up into my power as a man. organize. #empower. and actually believe it it! a few of the profound shift that happened along the way:

1. learned not to give a #fuck about what people think about me. i am a man. i have #emotions, #desires, needs, strengths, weaknesses, and they are all perfect. so often - as a man - i have found myself feeling as if i need to be strong all the time- but now i see so much beauty, even in the pain, #trauma, and #triumph of my brothers.

2. i gained an entirely new perception on the importance of values like honor (sacred union of the masculine and feminine), integrity (to myself and the other), kindness, and service (how are you showing up for your brothers)? these all deepened in my heart and mind this week as i began to revise my core values, as a man.

3. radical transparency- showing up to every situation with child- like curiosity, yet boldly speaking truth- even if it has the potential to scare someone away... essentially- in regards to the feminine- i aim to be able to speak my truth in order to no the #righteously aligned tribe will survive. 
4. #sacredsexuality- overall, a theme i see in my own life and through this retreat is the divine reunion of the sacred #masculine and #feminine. more on this soon.. my mind and heart are wide open

text:
according to the united nations office on drugs and crime’s global report on trafficking in persons, human trafficking has “hit a 13-year record high..” in 2016, there were over 25,000 cases of human trafficking reported, a 5,000 increase from 2003. although cases are being reported more consistently, with over 65 countries implementing different institutions to assist in collecting information, trafficking remains a crucial issue. there is no reason for a person to have a price tag on them. while progress has been made, we must continue to advocate for an end to this horrific occurrence happening across the globe. (photo credit: @unicef) •
•

text:
babylon tings

the man wants to control how we talk about white supremacy. how we even express frustration with hate crimes. we are required to use a language of inclusion, love, solidarity, and take some of the responsibility ourselves as people of color and difference who have been eating shit since day one. 
i refuse!

i have a modest proposal for white people. the next time there are hateful acts from your community, stand up, take responsibility, and examine how you have been complicit. how has your mind state, consumption, voting patterns, or even just apathy enabled and perpetuated white supremacy. do you complain about a “welfare state”? do you complain about mexicans taking your jobs?  did you support single payer? have you ever talked about genetics and extra ligaments when watching ussain bolt run? look back perhaps on how youve responded when the #metoo movement started. rewind the tape on your feelings during the kavanaugh hearings? where were you at the bar, at work, or in class when people were screaming to invade iraq in the early-aughts? do you speak about the “inherent violence” in the quran? do you ever consider how the imf and world bank is bleeding the carribean to death? where were u for puerto rico during the hurricanes? 
if you arent consistently with us shooting in the gym on all fronts, you are complicit. you dont get to wake up when you want and post a victim of a hate crime like “yo this is so fucked up we all human why is it this way? i love my black friends. go patriots tho!” the next time a lil chinaman tells you to clean your shit up, maybe don’t make it about you and your proximity to white supremacy. i dont care about your personal history or proximity to white supremacy. i just want it to end. that should be the focus. dont make it about you, make it about ending white supremacy because that is what still underlies every thing in this country. please and thank you.

i have a modest proposal for white people. the next time there are hateful acts from your community, stand up, take responsibility, and examine how you have been complicit. how has your mind state, consumption, voting patterns, or even just apathy enabled and perpetuated white supremacy. do you complain about a “welfare state”? do you complain about mexicans taking your jobs?  did you suppo single payer? have you ever talked about genetics and extra ligaments when watching ussain bolt run? look back perhaps on how youve responded when the  movement staed. rewind the tape on your feelings during the kavanaugh hearings? where were you at the bar, at work, or in class when people were screaming to invade iraq in the early-aughts? do you speak about the “inherent violence” in the quran? do you ever consider how the imf and world bank is bleeding the carribean to death? where were u for pueo rico during the hurricanes? 
if you arent consistently with us shooting in the gym on all fronts, you are complicit. you do not get to wake up when you want and post a victim of a hate crime like “yo this is so fucked up we all human why is it this way? i love my black friends. go patriots tho!” the next time a lil chinaman tells you to clean your shit up, maybe don’t make it about you and your proximity to white supremacy. i do not care about your personal history or proximity to white supremacy. i just want it to end. that should be the focus. do not make it about you, make it about ending white supremacy because that is what still underlies every thing in this country. please and thank you.

.
spirit, come. in portland as it is in heaven.
.
let’s gooooo! 💪🏼🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🙏🏼🙏🏼

text:
.
“love you, that’s why i hit you”
.
“we’re the only ones who love you enough to shun you”
.
“i had to monitor all your emails because i love you and you weren’t talking to me”
.
and on and on it goes.

you can  leave behind the toxic, the cruel, the gaslighting, the control, the manipulation... but then comes the great and holy work of redefining what love is. the mighty effort to rise up and love in ways that are honoring, good, and true. to find ways to express love that are authentic and smile into the divine presence inside the ones we love.
when someone says to me “i love you” it can be hard to know what they mean. but i’m learning.

i am glad you are here with me

#wildandholy #shunning #lovewins #loveiskind #truelove #metoo #marriagetoo #lifeafterdivorce #divorce #freetobe #newtricks

text:
#truththursday .
what is the difference between me in my 20’s and me in my 30’s? 
how i face obstacles, i used to analyze and overthink it. 
now i bulldoze through, i don’t want to waste more time. 
i know what i have overcome, i know who i am, so no more stopping me myself  from moving forward. 
i was my biggest downfall. i got sick of fighting. 
duck that! my middle name is adversity, i accept it and i grow from it.
video on my fb page coming soon about what slowed me down in life and how i became stronger for it.

text:
#tbt 
i spoke at the opening event for a women’s conference last april in #sanfrancisco . i got to meet the lovely @ashley_judd. i am in awe of ashley and all the amazing women like her who speak up for #women and #womenempowerment. #pbwc. i meet women in every capacity of life, business and society who look out for one another and are working to make the world better. we can each make a difference and i speak up on issues that matter. your voice matters. this women’s event had me energized and inspired. •
sometimes speaking up feels scary and isolating. even if no one stands up with you, it does not change your truth or the fact that others have their stories. and sometimes all it takes is a few brave people to stand up and inspire other people to stand up as they find their voice. never underestimate yourself and the power of speaking up. •
such sisterhood. when we rise together, we make change. speak up, rise up. #womenliftingwomen #thursdaymotivation #tbt #sanfrancisco #laugh #love #picoftheday #business #conferencespeaker #metoo #timesup #womenbosses #riseuptogether

anger is the surface feeling. there are tons of emotions underneath. when you get angry, it rattles you and no one else. it took a long time for me to learn this. i spent a long time asking why me, why did this happen. and it was simple, some people are toxic and dangerous. being empowered allowed me to move on. but being angry held me back for so long.
.

text_retweet:
#desgenerantelraval 
www.desgenerant.ateneudelraval.com ・・・
en abril de 2008 bernardo montoya, durante un permiso penitenciario, intentó agredir sexualmente a una joven de 27 años que paseaba con su perro pastor alemán. este, evitó la violación pero se llevó una puñalada con un cuchillo de 15 cm. como en él estaban las huellas de bernardo, la policía lo detuvo. resultó absuelto de intento de violación y solo se le condenó por agredir al perro. una vez más, no se creyó a la víctima.

como bernardo no tenía antecedentes por intento de violación, no figuraba en el registro de agresores sexuales. sí tenía antecedentes por asesinato. de forma que en cuanto laura desapareció, la policía no entró inmediatamente en la casa de bernardo, su vecino. 
aunque laura estuvo retenida allí.

hoy la familia de laura luelmo exige al estado español disculpas públicas y el cumplimiento íntegro de las penas. pero bernardo montoya no tenía condena ni estaba registrado por violación. 
recordemos que en el causa de diana quer su agresor también había sido absuelto de una violación. 
esto es lo que sucede cuando no crees a la víctima. 
si te resistes, te matan. si no te resistes no te creen, el agresor sigue libre y viola a la siguiente.
¿hasta cuando? 
#niunamenos #vivasnosqueremos #libreslindasylocas #feminismo #yositecreo #metoo

text: see what people are saying about candy apple butterscotch, #newauthor rebecca macceile’s debut publication. “this is an impactful read if you have ever experienced any sort of abuse. i appreciate the author’s candor and willingness to write with such openness. she takes responsibility for herself as much as she describes the lasting effects of trauma.” “it is worth the read. it’s about a woman empowered and, my god, that is a wonderful thing indeed.” “the author gets to the point while still painting a very clear and definite picture for the readers and i love that. the accounts of the trauma are laid out in such a way that you know what’s happening and are able to imagine it but you aren’t bombarded with intense graphic imagery, which i appreciate as a survivor myself. would definitely recommend!” “this amazingly written gem takes you inside the author’s world and keeps you there, making you feel like a discreet “bug on the wall.” i could not put it down.” “i wish everyone would write a memoir. it would be so much easier to understand people. i haven’t been through anything as violent or traumatic, but i think this story is relatable in a lot of ways. it just makes me see a lot of things differently in every day life. it’s a big eye opener.” #onsalenow at the #linkinbio. #kindle and #paperback versions available! also for members of #amazonprime, candy apple butterscotch is available in the #kindlelendinglibrary as well as through #kindleunlimitedbooks! that’s right you can read for #free. #nonfictionbooks #memoir #metoo #ptsdsurvivor #kindlestoryteller2018  #kindledirectpublishing #onsalenow #paperback #kindlelendinglibrary #bookrecommendations #indieauthor #authorsofinstagram #amazon

text: my grandmother.  she always wanted to go to new york and “read”. but of course being born in 1889, there weren’t many choices. but i wonder if she could have?  is what kept her in the farm the same thing that keeps me off screen?  perhaps it’s a mind set. after all there was stage back then. sarah bernhardt, theda bara, mrs. patrick campbell, mae west, fannie brice...and these are only the ones i can think of off the top of my head.  is a positive attitude genetic?  is depression hereditary?  how much can i accomplish if i just say i will?  how do i climb out of this sinkhole i’ve dug around me?  it’s like eating an elephant - one bite at a time.  #filmmaker #actor #writer #producer #sherlockholmes #generalsherman  #metoo #enoughisenough #wimps #womensempowerment #womensissues #women #gokingsgo #love

text:
#whatiwaswearing
.
this is what i was wearing on “the night”. the night that changed life forever.
.
i was wearing my ironman tank top. my dad bought me this tank top after cheering me on in the cold, wet rain for 14 hours and 11 minutes at ironman arizona in 2015. we bought it together in ironman village as my mom was chasing around my little boys only 6 and 4 at the time. ironman arizona was one of the proudest moments of my life. completing 140.6 miles on the coldest day arizona had all year, surrounded by my family and best friends. it was a dream. ❤️
.
and then just a few years later, i was wearing this tank top. the one that represented pure joy, grit and made me smile each time i wore it ... and every ounce of joy was stripped from my terrified body when my worst nightmare came true.
this tank top.
ironman.
triathlon.
it all made me cringe remembering the aftermath of trauma. 6...7...8...months later trying to pick up the pieces of my life and sobbing alone in the darkness. .
i did complete another ironman. untrained. to prove i was “ok”. to myself and everyone. but deep down my joy had been stripped from me and i was numb. and i started dropping races. oceanside 70.3, holidayman olympic and something i haven’t talked about yet ... ironman louisville. i had to drop out and was fully refunded. i was supposed to toe the line of ironman 3 in 2018 in louisville. but now i’m thankful i didn’t.
.
my joy for my sport was stolen. i was numb for soooooo long. i hurt and cried and have been through the worst personal hell imaginable. and every time i flashback i see this tank top. that is why i didn’t compete last year. that is why i probably blew it with two incredible companies i wanted to work with that took a chance on me....but for nothing i did wrong except the inability to deliver even one race...will likely back out for 2019. i couldn’t face triathlon....
.
until now.
.
and now it’s personal. after 10 months (and still ongoing) of intense therapy and my retreat in september... my mindset has shifted. i am here. i am fucking here. i am ready to take back what was stolen from me.
continued in comments👇🏽

and then just a few years later, i was wearing this tank top. the one that represented pure joy, grit and made me smile each time i wore it ... and every ounce of joy was stripped from my terrified body when my worst nightmare came true.
this tank top.
ironman.
triathlon.
it all made me cringe remembering the aftermath of trauma. 6...7...8...months later trying to pick up the pieces of my life and sobbing alone in the darkness. .
i did complete another ironman. untrained. to prove i was “ok”. to myself and everyone. but deep down my joy had been stripped from me and i was numb. and i started dropping races. oceanside 70.3, holidayman olympic and something i haven’t talked about yet ... ironman louisville. i had to drop out and was fully refunded. i was supposed to toe the line of ironman 3 in 2018 in louisville. but now i’m thankful i didn’t.
.
my joy for my sport was stolen. i was numb for soooooo long. i hurt and cried and have been through the worst personal hell imaginable. and every time i flashback i see this tank top. that is why i didn’t compete last year. that is why i probably blew it with two incredible companies i wanted to work with that took a chance on me....but for nothing i did wrong except the inability to deliver even one race...will likely back out for 2019. i couldn’t face triathlon....
.
until now.
.
and now it’s personal. after 10 months (and still ongoing) of intense therapy and my retreat in september... my mindset has shifted. i am here. i am fucking here. i am ready to take back what was stolen from me.
continued in comments👇🏽

.

on the dangers of pathologizing manhood

“the two fundamental objectives in the evolutionary game of life are to first survive (natural selection) and then to mate (sexual selection). for sexually reproducing species, including humans, evolution has endowed males and females with universal mating preferences that map onto sex-specific recurring challenges faced by each sex during our evolutionary history.
.
female fiddler crabs and hens prefer males with extravagantly large claws and tails respectively. ewes (female rams) will mate with the ram that wins the brutal intrasexual head-butting contest. they reward targeted aggression by granting sexual access. needless to say, there are innumerable other examples of sexual selection that i might describe, but i suspect that you get the general gist. are rams exhibiting toxic masculinity? are female fiddler crabs succumbing to antiquated notions of masculinity as promulgated by the crab patriarchy?
.
let’s now apply the exact same evolutionary process (sexual selection) to humans. evolutionary psychologists have documented universal patterns of mating preferences that are invariant across time and place. in no culture ever studied have women repeatedly preferred to mate with pear-shaped, low-status, tepid men possessing high-pitched, nasal voices. in no documented culture do women’s sexual fantasies revolve around granting sexual access to unemployed, unambitious men who occupy the lowest stratum of the social hierarchy. instead, women are attracted to “toxic masculine” male phenotypes that correlate with testosterone, and they are desirous of men who are socially dominant, who are strategically risk-taking in their behaviors, and who exhibit patterns of behaviors that will allow them to ascend the social hierarchy and defend their positions from encroachers. of course this does not imply that women are not attracted to intelligent, sensitive, kind, warm, and compassionate men. the ideal man is rugged and sensitive; masculine and caring; aggressive in some pursuits and gentle in others.” #thebestmencanbe #gillette #metoo

text:
damp suns in disturbed skies
20” x 16”. oil on linen. 2018 (title references baudelaire, a favorite poet of jo’s)
‘pink houses, charleston’ watercolor by jo nivison hopper. courtesy of the arthayer r. sanborn hopper collection trust. 
in 1924, the year of her marriage to edward hopper, jo nivison hopper was a well received artist in the new york art world - often shown in exhibitions alongside the likes of stuart davis and man ray. 
as an accomplished artist who eagerly embraced the most current modernist styles of the day, much more so than her husband did, jo captured in her vibrant and lyrical watercolors favored objects and sunny views of the scenic locales that she and edward often painted side by side.
this small building facing the cobblestones of chalmers street in historic charleston is commonly referred to as the pink house. built around 1712, it is believed to be the oldest remaining structure in the city. though called a house, the building originally served as a tavern and is rumored to have housed a brothel on the top floor.

.

text:
det var efter #metoo som sebastian nilsson, 31, bestämde sig för att han ville samla in pengar till en organisation som står upp för kvinnor. 👊💕han hittade kvinna till kvinna genom @linneaclaeson.

konceptet blev enkelt men effektivt. ✊ för varje kram han fick under 2018 la han undan en krona. 💸 samtidigt uppmanade han andra att engagera sig på facebook.
– jag gör egen musik och har satsat på att lägga upp mina musikklipp och be folk att gilla och dela, med motivationen att jag kommer att skänka pengar till kvinna till kvinna. det har varit en riktig win-win!

totalt fick han ihop 8 226 kronor! 👏👏 stort tack till sebastian och alla våra andra givare som engagerar sig genom att starta insamlingar. ❤️🌍 era bidrag till en mer jämställd värld är ovärderliga.

#kvinnatillkvinna
#kvinnorsrättigheter
#jämställdhet

text: a year ago today on january 30, 2018, something happened to me that kind of changed my life. this something had traumatized me. not only did i change as a person, but my mental illnesses got worse. since then, ive grown and became stronger, i made a best friend, and i've learned a lot about myself. im still finding ways to deal with my trauma, but i will never give up. i will continue to grow, even when i have a flashback or anxiety attack. my best friend helped me throughout all this, as we helped each other. all of my friends have helped me in some way, so has my best friend's family. thank you all for helping me for the past year, even when it seemed impossible. i love you all, i can't wait for the future and to get this traumatic event passed me, i can do it. my trauma doesnt define me or the person who was involved. i love my best friend and i wouldn't change what happened. im finally ready for the next chapter of my life. #metoo

text:
oftentimes, our struggle around safe sexual experiences is rooted in a secret developmental history of emotional neglect. yep — the early childhood experiences we had of either receiving the interpersonal nourishment we needed, or not, wires us into embodied expectations around what’s normal... .
_
for example, when our caretakers denied, downplayed, diminished or ignored our physical or emotional needs, we might’ve learned through osmosis to either deny them ourselves, embrace them with deviance or be hyper self-reliant around getting them met... .
_
having a regulated relationship to knowing, expressing and receiving our needs can be incredibly hard — foreign feeling, even. which is why it’s so common for many of us to instead end up in sexual experiences that mirror our developmental experience of our feelings and needs not mattering.
_
as adults wanting healthy, nourishing and fulfilling sex lives, beginning to identify our needs and leaning into the vulnerability of voicing them... is central.
_
do you know what physical safety feels like for you in a relationship? how about in bed? do you know what emotional safety feels like for you — in a relationship and in bed? 
_
identifying what you need in order to feel safe is the first step to truly fulfilling sex. voicing your needs is the second. and then, of course, mmmm... receiving. ❤️ .
_
some things that make meeee feel safe in bed: easy communication before, during & after, body praise & worship, mutual emotional admiration and respect, sharing std statuses, trusting i feel comfortable enough to pause if needed, trusting they’ll honor my pause, feeling free to be wild or tender or sad or soft or totally rolling in ecstasy.
_
what about you??
_
check my stories for the next 24 hrs for more on the link between developmental neglect & sexual exploitation. xo
_
sending you so much trust and care wherever you are on the journey!

life isn’t always easy, heartbreaks, loss of all sorts of things can bring us to our knees. it’s debilitating, it’s depressing and it is hell! yet, you have invisible wings and we can fly!

a woman’s strength isn’t just about how much she can handle before she breaks. it’s also about how much she must handle after she’s broken. #unknown 
what a beautiful thing it is to be able to stand tall and say i fell apart-over and over and over again & i survived & i will continue to #survive-because now i got it, i get it, i will survive it all! 
life isn’t always easy, heartbreaks, loss of all sorts of things can bring us to our knees. it’s debilitating, it’s depressing and it is hell! yet, you have invisible wings and we can fly!
#aerialsilks #aerialyoga #flyhighyoga 
@@@@@@@

i did nothing to deserve this.

i did nothing to deserve to have my relationship with my stepson destroyed.

i did nothing to deserve to have my relationship with my step sons girlfriend destroyed. 
i did nothing to have my relationship with my stepdaughter destroyed. 
i did not destroy her daughter.

text_retweet:
#repost @womensmarchjkt (@get_repost)
・・・
update, 18.30 wib, 31 jan: kuota sudah penuh.  terima kasih atas ketertarikannya. nanti akan ada facebook live juga.

setelah kasus kekerasan seksual yang dialami seorang mahasiswi bernama agni di ugm diekspos oleh pers mahasiswa setempat, balairung press, ada peledakan pembahasan tentang kekerasan seksual di kampus universitas di seluruh indonesia.

tetapi kasus agni bukan kasus kekerasan seksual pertama yang terjadi di kampus, dan tentu bukan kasus terakhir. sayang sekali, banyak korban belum pernah mendapatkan keadilan dan malah diremehkan, dirundung, diintimidasi, dan dikeluarkan universitas.

mengapa kekerasan seksual sering terjadi di kampus universitas, dan dilakukan baik mahasiswa maupun dosen? apakah gerakan #metoo yang sudah sangat mengubah perilaku dan cara berpikir di negara lain bisa berhasil di indonesia juga? dan bagaimana kita bisa membantu menghilangkan kekerasan seksual di kampus?

jakarta feminist discussion group (jfdg) dan yayasan pantau menyelenggarakan 'diskusi kekerasan seksual dan gerakan #metoo di kampus' sebagai bagian dari rangkaian pra-acara women's march jakarta pada sabtu, 9 februari 2019 pukul 9.30 s.d. 13.00 wib di ruang komunal (facebook), one pacific place, senayan.

dimoderatori febriana firdaus (wartawan, jakarta), diskusi ini dihadiri pembicara
1. citra maudy (reporter, balairung press, universitas gadjah mada, yogyakarta)
2. evi mariani (editor, the jakarta post, jakarta)
3. saras dewi (dosen, universitas indonesia, depok)

sekalian ada ada penyerahan oktovianus pogau award kepada citra dan thovan dari balairung press @bppmbalairung yogyakarta untuk keberanian dalam jurnalisme. selengkapnya ada di http://pantau.or.id/?/=d/789 
registrasi bisa dilakukan di formulir berikut. tempat terbatas!

text:
today she came through, 
through, with a scar on her hand,
with a bruise under the heart,
with a feel inside the chest,
cherishing a dwindling mess.
today she came with blood spilled all over,
tear-stained wound rolling,
marks unread, feelings unsaid,
words kept short and sentences incomplete,
yet, yet her punctuations were made very clear.
defined were the stops, they were fuller,
un-done, un-shed, unread,
her wounds increased,
they were more in halves, yet, deeper.
red turned blue, blue turned black,
white was unseen, yet peace more prominent,
she now wore more smiles than skirts,
more sleeves than leaves, more vain than pain.
her eyes spoke a thousand words,
her pupils dilated into nothingness, 
her lips chapped and her knuckles cracked,
her waist now, half the length. 
distances had reduced, but a bit too much,
peace or harmony, nothing as such,
blood dripped more but realisation struck less,
as sulking low had made her a big bad mess.
she was stuck yet resistant,
bold yet quiet,
known yet misunderstood,
she was like her dripping blood;
there, but unaware.
ages later, there were marks still,
scratches more, clots more, feels, less.
she gave in, gave in to the life and monotony,
that barely there symphony,
but she radiated unsaid energy,
she was powerful. she was made from the scars.
yet, her eyes numb, now spoke a thousand words,
her daughter came in the other day,
deep wounds, and blood dripping.
deep wounds. and,
blood dripping. -neeti

text:
my podcast @derekmansplains  is on hiatus currently but we will be dropping new episodes starting february 11th! in the meantime, here is a little #tbt to some episodes that i think are worth your time if you haven't listened yet! please subscribe, rate, review on @itunes @spotify and @stitcher give feedback at dmiapod@gmail.com! and check these eps to hold you over until 2/11!
-
-
ep. 3: "harv as a rock"w/anne victoria clark: my friend, comedian and tour mate anne clark talks with me about the #metoo movement, my bike getting stolen and being a viral sensation via dwayne "the rock" johnson's quoting of her work! anne has a new podcast called "the anne clark show" available on @itunes and stitcher. follow her on twitter: @annevclark
-
-
ep. 29: "chick-fil-gay" w/wanjiko eke: comedian wanjiko eke sits down to discuss her life as a gay black comic, my rose colored nostalgia and fake liberals! wanjiko has a new show in brooklyn called "rif comed: resistance is fertile" at pete's candy store. follow her on twitter: @wanjikoiam
-
-
ep. 33: "the lost science of science" w/dr. raj sivaraman: are white people at the top of the cultural food chain? is climate change real? dr. sivaraman is a comic, microbiologist and runner up on jeopardy. raj hosts a comedy show in new york called "monotony" where comedians and storytellers dive deep into the history of the most mundane things they are obsessed with. follow raj on twitter at: @rajsivaraman
-
-
ep. 40: "exploring whiteness" w/bryan yang. comic and writer bryan yang talk about his georgia roots, the hmong people and the man himself; ric flair! brian can be seen opening for the daily shows ronny chieng and you can follow him on twitter at: @bryanyang
-
-
ep. 43: "guys named brett" w/alison leiby. my wife joins alison and i to discuss the day-of appointment of supreme court justice brett kavanaugh and how they feel it affects the perception of women and their value as people. alison is a very funny comic who's written for "the opposition with jordan klepper", "the president show" and is now working on season 3 of the emmy and golden globe winning show "the marvelous mrs. maisel." follow alison on twitter at: @alisonlieby
