text:
my podcast @derekmansplains  is on hiatus currently but we will be dropping new episodes starting february 11th! in the meantime, here is a little #tbt to some episodes that i think are worth your time if you haven't listened yet! please subscribe, rate, review on @itunes @spotify and @stitcher give feedback at dmiapod@gmail.com! and check these eps to hold you over until 2/11!
-
-
ep. 3: "harv as a rock"w/anne victoria clark: my friend, comedian and tour mate anne clark talks with me about the #metoo movement, my bike getting stolen and being a viral sensation via dwayne "the rock" johnson's quoting of her work! anne has a new podcast called "the anne clark show" available on @itunes and stitcher. follow her on twitter: @annevclark
-
-
ep. 29: "chick-fil-gay" w/wanjiko eke: comedian wanjiko eke sits down to discuss her life as a gay black comic, my rose colored nostalgia and fake liberals! wanjiko has a new show in brooklyn called "rif comed: resistance is fertile" at pete's candy store. follow her on twitter: @wanjikoiam
-
-
ep. 33: "the lost science of science" w/dr. raj sivaraman: are white people at the top of the cultural food chain? is climate change real? dr. sivaraman is a comic, microbiologist and runner up on jeopardy. raj hosts a comedy show in new york called "monotony" where comedians and storytellers dive deep into the history of the most mundane things they are obsessed with. follow raj on twitter at: @rajsivaraman
-
-
ep. 40: "exploring whiteness" w/bryan yang. comic and writer bryan yang talk about his georgia roots, the hmong people and the man himself; ric flair! brian can be seen opening for the daily shows ronny chieng and you can follow him on twitter at: @bryanyang
-
-
ep. 43: "guys named brett" w/alison leiby. my wife joins alison and i to discuss the day-of appointment of supreme court justice brett kavanaugh and how they feel it affects the perception of women and their value as people. alison is a very funny comic who's written for "the opposition with jordan klepper", "the president show" and is now working on season 3 of the emmy and golden globe winning show "the marvelous mrs. maisel." follow alison on twitter at: @alisonlieby
-
-

text:
dpr ri dukung ruu penghapusan kekerasan seksual

wakil ketua komisi viii dewan perwakilan rakyat (dpr) ace hasan syadzily membantah rancangan undang-undang (ruu) penghapusan kekerasan seksual (pks) diarahkan untuk mendukung pro-zina dan lesbian, gay, biseks, dan transgender (lgbt) "jadi tidak benar jika ada pandangan yang berkembang selama ini bahwa ruu pks akan diarahkan pada upaya memperbolehkan hubungan seksual suka sama suka [free sex] dan memperbolehkan hubungan seks sesama jenis," ujar ace, kamis (31/1/2019). terkait dengan ruu pks, ace menjelaskan sampai saat ini dpr komisi viii masih melakukan pembahasan di tingkat panitia kerja (panja). kata ace, dpr telah sepakat dengan panja pemerintah untuk membahas daftar inventaris masalah (dim). "kami akan menyandingkan antara dim yang kami miliki dengan dim yang dimiliki pemerintah," ucap ace.

text:
en abril de 2008 bernardo montoya ,en un permiso  penitenciario, intentó agredir sexualmente a una joven de 27 años que paseaba con su perro pastor alemán. el perro evitó la violación pero se llevó una puñalada con un cuchillo de 15 cm. como en  el cuchillo estaban las huellas de bernardo, la policía lo detuvo. resultó absuelto de intento de violación y solo se le condenó por agredir al perro. una vez más, no se creyó a la víctima.

como bernardo no tenía antecedentes por intento de violación, no figuraba en el registro de agresores sexuales.( sí tenía antecedentes por asesinato). de forma que en cuanto laura desapareció, la policía no entró inmediatamente en la casa de bernardo, su vecinos. aunque laura estuvo retenida allí.

hoy la familia de laura luelmo ha exigido al estado español una disculpa pública y el cumplimiento íntegro de las penas. pero bernardo montoya no tenía condena por violación.  recordemos que en el causa de diana quer su agresor también había sido absuelto de una violación. 
esto es lo que sucede cuando no crees a la víctima. si te resistes, te matan. si no te resistes no te creen, el agresor sigue libre y viola a la siguiente.

para colmo hoy un chico de 19 años ha decapitado a una chica de 17. 17 años. como madre de una niña de 15 no puedo ni imaginar el dolor de sus padres. la violencia de género, lejos de disminuir,  se instala cada vez más en el imaginario de nuestros adolescentes.no podemos ni debemos permitir esto.

#niunamenos #vivasnosqueremos #libreslindasylocas #feminismo #yositecreo #metoo

text:
#terrycrews est l’un des rares hommes à hollywood à avoir brisé le silence, suite à l’affaire #weinstein, en témoignant de l’agression sexuelle dont il a été victime par un “ponte de l’industrie hollywoodienne” ainsi qu’il l’a expliqué dans une série de tweets. “j’espère que mon histoire dissuadera un prédateur et encouragera quelqu’un qui se sent désespéré à parler” a conclu l’acteur, qui joue le lieutenant #terryjeffords dans la série #brooklynninenine.

il a repris la parole, devant le sénat américain cette fois, en revenant sur cet épisode traumatisant pour dénoncer la “masculinité toxique” et pour défendre sexual assault survivors bill of rights, une loi proposée par #barackobama en son temps.
“j’ai vu énormément de jeunes hommes noirs céder à la violence après avoir été provoqués et, soit ils étaient mis en prison, soit ils étaient tués.” a-t-il déclaré pour expliquer pourquoi il ne s’était pas défendu ce jour là.

un grand geste de courage de la part de l’acteur qui dénonçait à buzzfeed la violence du monde hollywoodien : “quand quelqu’un prend la parole, on lui coupe la tête, pour que la prochaine personne garde le silence. »
le silence, terry crews lui l’a brisé, en mettant en péril sa carrière pour que cessent toutes les violences.
respect.

#wondher #lesalliés #hollywood #metoo #harveyweinstein #sexualassault #acteur #violences #violencessexuelles #silentbreakers #égalité #stopviolence #sexualviolence #féministe #feminism #menwithwomen

text:
book #11 for 2019 - the book of essie

wow. that’s my response to this book. just wow. i held off on reading it because i thought the whole premise was a bit cliche’ ... i don’t even want to watch reality tv, much less read a book about it. but after @annebogel read it and had good things to say, i decided to give it a chance. and i’m glad i did. it’s a great read, and i’m left with all kinds of pride over the bravery of the characters. ***⭐️ ⭐️ ⭐️ ⭐️***

text:
warwick university @universityofwarwick have banned 3 students after jokes about rape and racial slurs were exchange in a facebook group chat. 
screenshots of alleged racist, anti semitic and misogynistic messages - which included the remark ‘sometimes it’s fun to just go wild and rape 100 girls” were investigated by the university. .
.
one student has been banned from campus for life, and another two students have been banned for 10 years after formal complaints were made about the messages. two more students have been required to withdraw from the university for a year with immediate effect. 
as reported by @the.independent .
.
what is the cause of this behaviour? how is this acceptable? i’ve reported through our blog interviews young women’s experience at university. one was date raped and the other received sexual harassment and sexism working as a model. link in bio 👆🏻👆🏻👆🏻👆🏻to read @andhernameissian @laurennnkenny and these are not isolated rare incidence, they happened in everyday environments. one of the aims of future female is to look at how everyday habitual sexism may lead to more serious crimes. if we do not speak up about misogyny, racism, and antisemitic behaviour we are condoning. the language these young men have used is part of everyday. it’s deemed normal to many. calling it out when it begins will mean talking to teenagers and younger. we are interested in knowing who’s doing this type of work? .
.
.
#everydaysexism #womensupportwomen #pressforprogress #timesup #wearefuturefemale #raisingawareness #universityofwarwick #metoo #student #rapeculture #toxicmasculinity #talkingtoteenagers

.
.

nou dat was het geloof ik wel. nog nieuwe dingen gelezen?

text:
/ perempuan butuh syariat islam, bukan ruu pks /
.
pengamat politik dan pemerhati perempuan, pratama julia sunjandari, menilai alasan tingginya angka kekerasan seksual di indonesia yang menjadi latar belakang legalisasi rancangan undang undang (ruu) penghapusan kekerasan seksual (pks) sungguh mengada-ada.
.
pasalnya, menurut pratma, bukan sekadar ada umbrella act lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai. perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya atau gerakan #metoo yang kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual.
.
pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, “pertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai ‘amanah’ beijing platform for action (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa ‘kontrol seksual’ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.”
.
kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagi qawwam (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah.
.
“menjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,” ungkapnya kepada mnews, rabu (30/1/2019).
.
.
——
follow @muslimahnewsid
.

text:
great morning everyone! happy friday! happy ujima day! the new year is rapidly approaching! i’m still taking donations towards my book project. i truly appreciate the donations i have gotten so far! if you donate towards the book publishing this is what you receive: 💜whoever sponsors $30-$75 gets a free autographed copy 💜whoever sponsors $100-$250, gets an free autographed copy and a t-shirt 💜whoever sponsors $500 or more, gets a free autographed copy, t-shirt, a goodie bag from yours truly, and/or 2 complimentary full makeup services 
i can send you the link personally or you can go on my page and click the link in bio. i’m taking donations until january 25, 2019. please share this post if you cannot contribute or even if you can please share as well and donate. with god’s help and with your financial donation, i want to help these women who have dealt with this live and maybe just maybe my book will help. i believe that i’m one of the voices of many women who remain silent and are afraid to share their scars of domestic violence, losing their identity and experiencing abandonment. thank you for your time. have a great day and a happy and prosperous 2019❤️❤️❤️ #thekweenexperience #kweenpire #hismasterpiece #mymemoir #mytestimony #womenempoweringwomen #survivor #overcomer #domesticviolence #domesticviolenceisreal #domesticviolencesurvivor #lovedoesnthurt #fearisnotlove #loveissacred #domesticviolenceadvocate #metoo #womenpower #thebaldiemovement #empowerment #speaklife #ministry

text:
i have the honor tonight of designing a tablescape for hear our stories by @upsetting_rape at @motorhousebaltimore. this edition of hear our stories is about celebrating black victim-survivors. this table was a special one to design. i will be honoring my mother, my sister, ancestors, friends, strangers, and myself through a light meal dedicated to active healing in 2019. as with all of my tablescapes there will be symbolism to each element. 
there will be cacao butter chia cornbread made with @eatsoular cacao butter (symbolizing wealth as nourishing and healthy relationships with our bodies and ourselves) and a remix of the classic rice and black-eyed peas dish hoppin’ john (with the black eyed peas symbolizing the exploration of restorative justice in domestic violence, brown rice to symbolize prosperity in the path of healing, and adobo chiles to represent the concept of thriving versus surviving on the very linear path of healing). for even lighter nourishment i will also have my smoke on the water broth for sipping. it is a vegan broth i make with applewood smoked sun tea and garlic i ferment for 15 days. all foods served are vegan. please join us for this very special night of fellowship and reflection. #❤️#notalone #metoo #comestibledesign #fooddesign #tablescape #blackhealing #healingfoods

text:
i put my daughter on the bus minutes ago, and the chill won’t leave my bones. but you know what else leaves me stone cold? learning that former new york attorney general #ericschneiderman spent nearly $340,000 in campaign donations on lawyers. and specifically, on the lawyers representing him in investigations into his criminal sexual abuse of @mmanningbarish and others. theirs were the horrific stories, as retold by @newyorkermag, that led to his swift resignation last may.
....
campaign donations are supposed to help candidates amplify their message and publicize their accomplishments, not save them from felony charges. instead, new yorkers who gave schneiderman money when he was a national hero in the making unwittingly and unwillingly became his legal defense fund. this is sick, sad, and worst of all, legal in new york.
....
but #ericschneiderman did not just spent $340k of his voters’ trust on criminal defense lawyers. he is still sitting on another $6.5 million in his campaign war chest, built in part on his reputation as a vigorous voice for women’s equality. his reps now say he will distribute the money to “worthy and appropriate” causes. his victims are convinced he will give the money to yoga and meditation centers that will give him refuge in exchange for big bucks. there is only one “worthy and appropriate” cause here: women’s fight to be free from gender-based violence. many of us applauded eric schneiderman when he was a voice for choice. in my own life as an activist, i posed for pictures with him at fundraisers; gave him standing ovations at rallies. survivors and allies: #ericschneiderman may be gone from public view, but his actions still undermine our movement and threaten our bodies. let’s demand he give his money instead to orgs like @sffny @safehorizon and @timesup. #trustwomen #standwithsurvivors #michellemanningbarish #metoo

el salto tándem es una variación del paracaidismo convencional, en la cual un aprendiz de paracaidismo salta junto a un instructor unidos por medio de un sistema de doble arnés. precisa de una breve formación en tierra, donde se explican distintos aspectos del salto, principalmente relacionados con seguridad. se usa un arnés especial de tándem que se ciñe al cuerpo del estudiante. el salto se efectúa desde una altura que fluctúa entre los 5.000 y 2.700 metros sobre el nivel de la tierra, lo que da entre 75 a 25 segundos de caída libre. aproximadamente a 1.500 metros de altura se abre el paracaídas, quedando entre 5 y 10 minutos de vuelo para aterrizar.
.
.
.

text:
hello everyone! as many of you know i’m publishing a book in summer 2019. i have been sharing my excerpts and i have received a lot of great feedback from it. i believe what makes my book unique is that it is a raw, vivid, uncut story of an experience i went through in my life. i believe that i’m one of the voices of many women who remain silent and are afraid to share their scars of domestic violence, losing their identity and experiencing abandonment. i’m a domestic violence survivor and through my experience and with my book i know that it will help many women heal and get out of a toxic situation. this sponsorship program will help me get to my goal of publishing my book so i can help other women survive and thrive. here is what it entails: 💜whoever sponsors $30-$75 gets a free autographed copy 💜whoever sponsors $100-$250, gets an free autographed copy and a t-shirt 💜whoever sponsors $500 or more, gets a free autographed copy, t-shirt, a goodie bag from yours truly, and/or 2 complimentary full makeup services

today i read about a woman who was found dead by her 4 young children. she was a victim of domestic violence. with god’s help and with your financial donation, i want to help these women who have dealt with this live and maybe just maybe my book will help. if you want the link to donate, please press the link in my bio or i’ll leave the link in the comments below. please share this. thank you all so much for your time. have a blessed day 💜💜 #thekweenexperience #kweenpire #hismasterpiece #mymemoir #mytestimony #ephesians210 #aspiringauthor #author #blackauthors #blackwomenauthors #womenempoweringwomen #survivor #overcomer #domesticviolence #domesticviolenceisreal #domesticviolencesurvivor #lovedoesnthurt #fearisnotlove #loveissacred #domesticviolenceadvocate #metoo #womenpower #thebaldiemovement #empowerment #speaklife #ministry

text:
let’s try something out shall we?
.
if i ask “how are you?” you respond how...i’m good, fine, okay usually right?

see, technically those aren’t feelings they are just safe, surface level fillers we all (hi #metoo ) use because it’s easy and we are programmed to automatically respond in social interactions.

okay, now let’s try this: how’s your heart?

see what i did there? i didn’t ask how are you so you could just skip the saga and fill it with a good fine whatever. i asked how your heart is. which sure, you could say fine but my bet is you’re going to respond with the truth. you’re going to give me more depth.

we can embrace our humanness, be more real and redefine how we connect by first simply shifting our language and how we talk to one another.

i’ve been deliberately asking this to everyone i come in contact with over the last year and let me tell ya, it’s amazing what happens when you give someone some breathing room to be real.

try it out. ask your bff, your coworker, your mom, the barista. report back. let’s #relcaimwhatsreal by connecting heart to heart
💕
#hearttalk #howsyourheart #letstalk #realtalk #humanaf #womensupportingwomen #grlpwr #inthistogether #bevulnerable #becourageous #connection #wordstoinspire #iamwellandgood
name: SOUL CONNECT ✖️ KATIE KURTZ

text:
where will #metoo take its survivors? 
it’s a question that we, at the polis project, tried to deal with in our conversations last year even as women survivors were coming out with devastating, chilling testimonies, one after another. 
considering the history of silence, it isn’t a surprise that most conversations in the media remained confined to survivor testimonies per se. in an effort to add to the larger conversation, we began with an obvious question: what was “next” for the survivors, those who remained anonymous and those who came out to identify their perpetrators? how do we understand the culture of fear and silence that remains? what did #metoo mean in hard, legal terms for the victims, and the perpetrators? or, what kind of legal challenges did survivor testimonies raise, and for whom? how could the survivors possibly face these challenges, particularly considering their vulnerability on one hand and, often, the power and influence of the men they accused? what paths lead to justice? is there anything that can vastly minimize sexual violence? 
the work that’s emerged thereafter couldn’t be confined to these questions—there can be no clarity towards the future without constantly delving in the past, and the present. this small body of work seeks to do that without taking its eyes off the question: what comes “after” #metoo? 
beginning tomorrow, the polis project will publish work featuring apoorva karagappa, jhuma sen, kruthika ns, nayema nasir, raya sarkar, rollie mukherjee, suchitra vijayan, and vasundhara sirnate. 
do read, and share! 
write to us at feedback@thepolisproject.com.

warning: sexual assault/harassment/rape

i was 15, he was 16. he was my first boyfriend. we did (unfortunately still do) karate together. we had been dating for 2 months and he started pushing the idea of sex. i told him no every time. on february 4th of this year, we were alone in his basement in his bedroom and he threw me down on his bed and started aggressively making out with me. i couldn't get away. i tried turning my head and kicking my legs and and yelling for him to stop. but it was useless, he had me pinned down and my arms above my head, his tongue down my throat and if i yelled anymore i might puke. it seemed like an eternity. he put his hands up my shirt and groped my butt and my boobs and when i moved his hand, he moved it back. i told him no, he said it's fine just kissing! it is not fine! it was not just kissing! this happened more than once during the six months we dated. i only consented to kissing him maybe twice. 
he is the reason i don't trust men, the reason i'm terrified to date. i can't even handle being in class with him at karate. i had a panic attack last week as soon as i walked off that floor because he was next to me the whole class grinning. i don't even know how i hold myself together. i see home every single day at school, he stares at me during lunch and across the hall from his classroom into mine. i wish he could feel the pain he put me through. 
i feel like that day is all i think about. the fact that i know i'm not the only one he assulted, and there is nothing that i can do to protect anyone from him because they won't believe he could do such a thing. he seems like a nice, innocent guy until you're alone with him. i reported it, but he is still walking, and taunting me every single day of my life. this "sweet innocent" guy hit me and hurt me in ways that will affect me and other girls for the rest of our lives. and the worst part is that so many others have gone through the same thing and these pigs feel no remorse. #metoo #metoomovement #nomore

text:
this photo is a snapshot of a workshop i’m leading as the @laffcharity youth development coordinator with the girls of @mantayperu. in this session, we are discussing their rights as girls and young women. the right to say no to unwanted sex. the right to ask a man to wear a condom. the right to speak up for what they want. “women and girls have always faced hurdles. but that’s never stopped us. we’ve sacrificed, fought, campaigned, succeeded, been knocked back, and succeeded again. in a race for justice, we’ve leapt over countless obstacles to win our rights.” -emma watson
.
📷🌎 cusco, peru
.
#sheinspiresproject #girlsaroundtheworld #girlpower #girls #genderequality #selflove #diversity #sexualhealth #girlsrights #yourrighttosayno #womensrights #humanrights #metoo #niunamenos

text:
#whitewednesdays majid azizi is a courageous man living in iran 🇮🇷 who could not stand by while the women of iran were attacked and abused by the corrupt oppressive authoritarian fascist regime of #alikhamenei and tinpot wannabe dictator #hoseinrohani . this man was jailed for supporting the women of iran and the #nocompulsoryhijab movement. the women will prevail over this criminal evil regime. democracy is fragile and must be fought for and protected. #freehijabprotesters #walkingunveiled #scanning #shepersisted #girlsofrevolutionstreet #girlpower #metoo #timesup #resist #saraamiirrii 
براي برادرم #مجيد_عزيزي ‎نامش مجید عزیزی است. تنها یک هفته بعد از اولین دختر خیابان انقلاب روی کاغذی نوشت دختر_خیابان_انقلاب_کجاست و شال سفیدی را در حمایت از او به چوب بست . آن زمان هنوز #دختران_خیابان_انقلاب  تکثیر نشده بودند و او اولین مردی بود که رفت به خیابان . هفته دوم باز هم رفت و‌اعتراض مدنی‌اش را تکرار کرد تا اینکه کم کم #دختران_خیابان_انقلاب تکثیر شدند و همین سوال را پرسیدند و مجید نیز اینبار با دختران خیابان انقلاب همراه شد و  در شهر شیراز روی سکو رفت و سرانجام بازداشت  و دادگاهی شد. #مجيد_عزيزي ۲۸ آبانماه ٩٧رفت به زندان #عادل_آباد برای گذراندن یک سال حبس تعزيري .
‎مجید کارشناس بازیگری سینماست ، از اولین مردانی بود که برای اعتراض به #حجاب_اجباری با کمپین #چهارشنبه_های_سفید و #دختران_خیابان_انقلاب ‎
همراه شد
‎ولی پاسخ اعتراض مدنی این بود که پس ازباز داشت وضرب و شتم توسط نيروهاي انتظامي و امنيتي، به جرم تبلیغ علیه نظام به یک سال زندان محکوم شد و حکم دردادگاه تجدید نظر هم تایید شد، در دادگاه با دستبند جلوی چشم مادرنگران وخانواده جهت اجرای حکم یک ساله به زندان عادل آباد شیراز رفت #مجید_عزیزی در صفحه اینستاگرام خود پستی گذاشت و نوشت من نمیتوانستم در برابر ظلم ستم تبعیض علیه زنان سکوت کنم. مجيد عليرغم بيماري قلبي بر اساس تصميم مسئولين زندان از دريافت دارو محروم است. ‎

text:
sain tilaisuuden osallistua riina rinteen ohjaamaan naisen halua käsittelevään dokumenttiin, joka löytyy nyt yle areenasta. @rinnerii on tehnyt mielettömän suuren työn koostaessaan valtavan suuresta aineistosta sen ydinsanoman: nainen, kuten kuka tahansa, on vapaa ilmaisemaan seksuaalisuuttaan, ja samalla tulla arvostetuksi, nähdyksi, kuulluksi ja kohdelluksi tasavertaisena ihmisenä.

olen opiskellut puolitoista vuotta seksuaali-, parisuhde- ja voimaantumisen henkilökohtaiseksi valmentajaksi. silti avoimesti omista haluista puhuminen sai tunnemylläkän aikaan. ja ehkä juuri siksi. olen sukeltanut syvälle naisten voiman, seksuaalisuuden ja halun piilottamisen mekanismeihin ja tullut tietoiseksi, kuinka kannan osaa tästä kivusta sisälläni.

olen tullut tietoisemmaksi niistä tekijöistä, joiden takia minä ja suuri osa naisista kokevat vapaan ja autenttisen seksuaalisen ilmaisun haastavana, jopa uhkaavana, ja millä tavalla tämä vaikuttaa omaan ja läheistemme elämään.

televisiossa omista seksimieltymyksistä ja -kokemuksista puhuminen on lähtökohtaisesti kuumottavaa (hei perhe, sukulaiset, kumppanit, vuokranantajat ja työnantajat!), mutta itselle oli merkittävää näyttää, miltä tämä tuntuu. häpeä ja pelko suhteessa omiin haluihin.

pelko siitä, että tulee leimatuksi tai tuomituksi, ja joiden alla piilee se kaikkein syvin ihmisolennon kauhukuva: tulla hylätyksi. hylätyksi tuleminen on tarkoittanut ihmisyksilölle kuolemaa, sillä ilman laumaa emme olisi selvinneet hengissä. tämä pelko juurtuneena primaariaivorakenteisiimme, on aika loogista, että normista poikkeaminen ja esiin tuleminen omana itsenä tuntuu uhkaavalta. 
niin moni meistä, itseni mukaan lukien, on joutunut kokemaan tämän elämässään konkreettisesti. kun itsensä näyttäminen ei ole ollut kannattavaa, vaan rangaistavaa ja tuomittavaa.

uskon, että vain kohtaamalla nämä pelot, häpeän, intiimit aiheet ja omat halumme itse, voimme astua omaan voimaamme, omistaa oman seksuaalisuutemme ja rajamme. tämä vie meidät kohti kaikkein suurinta rakkautta, nautintoa ja yhteyttä muiden ihmisten kanssa. 
#yleperjantai #yleareena #perjantaidokkari #haluavanainen #suostumus #metoo #sextalk #seksuaalisuus #voimaantuminen

text_retweet:
reposted from @muslimahnewsid - / perempuan butuh syariat islam, bukan ruu pks /
.
pengamat politik dan pemerhati perempuan, pratama julia sunjandari, menilai alasan tingginya angka kekerasan seksual di indonesia yang menjadi latar belakang legalisasi rancangan undang undang (ruu) penghapusan kekerasan seksual (pks) sungguh mengada-ada.
.
pasalnya, menurut pratma, bukan sekadar ada umbrella act lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai. perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya atau gerakan #metoo yang kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual.
.
pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, “pertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai ‘amanah’ beijing platform for action (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa ‘kontrol seksual’ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.”
.
kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagi qawwam (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah.
.
“menjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,” ungkapnya kepada mnews, rabu (30/1/2019).
.
.
——
follow @muslimahnewsid
.

#khilafahajaranislam

#tolakruupks

text:
a bedazzling lady, so bold and beautiful,
seeks a companion who for her is suitable.
she dreams of a man with a heart of gold,
searching for the one who would fit in her fantasy's mould.
she looks for,
beauty and valour personified in his every aspect,
with charm and grace his soul bedecked.
his smile, calm like the subtle waves of the sea,
like the string of pearls sparkling with glee.
his eyes, brilliant like a diamond so pure,
the dauntless pride in them graciously allure.
his moustache with pride they curl,
so gallant, a head-turner for every girl.
his chest strong and broad with honor, 
his charisma so magnetic, many hearts he conquer.
his love, like the a vivid pallet of million colors beams through his heart,
the virility in his soul is what makes him different, from others he's worlds apart.
all she wants is a chivalrous, courageous, gentleman for sure,
her perfect soulmate who, like her, is angelic to the core.
. ©shwetha @shwetha_rishi
________________________________
a woman needs and wants a man who is not afraid to show his sensitive side. who owns who he is with pride. who's not reluctant to show his love for her, who respects her and her family and her wishes. who works hard to make her dreams come true the same way he works for his. 
a woman seeks a gentleman who's the exact mirror image of her soul, the perfect soulmate.
#shespeaksforthechange #herstory #proudtobeawoman #girlpower #genderroles #genderequality #metoomovement #metoo  #she #her #sheisme #shespeaks #shewrites
name: She Speaks For The CHANGE ♀

text:
sheets of empty canvas
untouched sheets of clay
were laid spread out before me
as her body once did
all five horizons
revolved around her soul
as the earth to the sun
now the air i tasted and breathed
has taken a turn

oh and all i taught her was everything
oh i know she gave me all that she wore
and now my bitter hands
chafe beneath the clouds
of what was everything
oh the pictures have
all been washed in black
tattooed everything
i take a walk outside
i'm surrounded by
some kids at play
i can feel their laughter
so why do i sear
oh, and twisted thoughts that spin
round my head
i'm spinning
oh, i'm spinning
how quick the sun can, drop away

text:
на днях мне на рабочую почту пришло очередное приглашение-требование пройти тренинг.
⠀
всё бы ничего - мне их миллион приходит, и я уже ко всему привыкла, но когда я открыла именно это, то честно говоря, ошалела.
⠀
⠀
это был тренинг по борьбе с с*кс домогательствами на рабочем месте.
⠀
"что такого?", - спросите вы. а вот что - за 4 полных года в крупнейшей российской и мировой компании у меня ни разу не было этого тренинга! этика была, анти-взятки были, борьба с фишингом и электорнным мошенничеством была, а с домогательствами - нет, ни разу!
⠀
⠀
"ок, - подумала я, - всё же сейчас я работаю в другой компании, может у них и есть этот тренинг в россии, и я просто не знаю?" открыла доступные  языки - русского нет.
⠀
⠀
"это всё - разница менталитетов", - скажете вы. "да в америках принято репортить любой косой взгляд в сторону женщин!"
⠀
⠀
⠀
хм, нет. тренинг был о физическом (!) неадекватном поведении - девушку потрогали, простите, за сиськи, на глазах у всех, на выездном мероприятии.
⠀
⠀
обсудила с подругой и услышала мнение, что россия просто не готова к таким тренингам, тк даже анти-взяточничество заходит еле-еле. а вы как считаете?
⠀
⠀
⠀
p.s. "занимательная" (на самом деле - нет) статистика для тех, кто сомневается в существовании проблемы - по опросам в великобритании (не самая несдержанная страна, как считаете?) домогательствам на работе подвергалась... половина опрошенных женщин. по россии никаких данных нет.
⠀
⠀
#ocanadaaa_остросоц

text:
"it was deepika padukone who took a firm stand, saying people weren’t going to look at nuance & the mami had to take off movies that were associated with anybody who had been outed during the #metoo movement. her word carried weight & that’s what mami eventually did.” << i knew it, i knew she was behind that 👏👏❤ #proud
.
"deepika padukone as chairperson will ensure the festival gets the financial support it needs. as a board member she has been a commanding voice of reason in previous mami meetings. deepika said if her participation helped the broader cause of the festival, she was okay with it.
this decision was unanimous and the only person who had reservations was none other than deepika herself. she said how she wasn't entirely convinced on becoming the chairperson of the festival as she has little knowledge about it. deepika has also made it clear how this will not be a 5 year long commitment and she'd like to see how things go about in the first year"
.
"لقد كانت ديبيكا هي التي اتخذت موقفا حازما، قالت إن الناس لن ينظروا إلى الفارق البسيط وعلى مهرجان مامي سحب الأفلام التي ارتبطت بأي شخص تم اتهامة بحملة المي تو (حملة ضد التحرش). وهذا مافعله مهرجان مامي في النهاية" (تم سحب فلم المخرج والمنتج فيكاس بال بعد قضية التحرش)
.
"كون ديبيكا رئيسة المهرجان ستضمن حصوله على الدعم المالي الذي يحتاجه. بصفتها عضوا في مجلس الإدارة، كانت ذات صوتًا قياديًا عاقلا في اجتماعات مامي السابقة.
قرار اختيارها كان بالإجماع الشخص الوحيد الذي كان لديه تحفظات هي ديبيكا نفسها. قالت بأنها لم تكن مقتنعة تماما بأن تصبح رئيسة المهرجان حيث أنها لا تعرف الكثير عن ذلك. كما أوضحت ديبيكا انه لن يكون هذا الالتزام لمدة ٥ سنوات، تود أن ترى كيف تسير الأمور في السنة الأولى"
.
"قررت كيران التنحي كرئيسة لمامي لأنها أرادت التركيز على صنع فلم. كنا نفكر بالأسماء وشعر الجميع أن ديبيكا بادكون هي الشخص المناسب. انها فنانة رائعة. والآن هي أيضا جزء من مامي، هي عضوة في مجلس الإدارة لبضع سنوات وكانت داعمة للغاية، لذا طلبنا منها جميعا ان تقبل هذا المنصب وقالت 'نعم'. هي فنانة معروفة عالميا، وقد اثبتت براعتها كممثلة والأن ستصبح منتجه. وهي بالتأكيد تصنع أفلامًا جيدة"
.
.
والله كنت حاسه اول مانزل خبر فيكاس حسيت ان ديبيكا اهي اللي اقترحت هشي 👏👏❤
.
.

text:
ecologie ou puissance numérique : faut-il choisir ? 
dans cet épisode j’ai le plaisir de recevoir sophie @dambrosio.sophie - et accrochez-vous.

comme la plupart d’entre vous, je suis noyée chaque jour sous un déluge d’email. des newsletters, des promotions commerciales, des emails de travail, des mails de proches qui ont laisser tomber les cartes postales… au rayon des bonnes idées mais pas tant que ça, une voiture électrique, sortie d’usine, a déjà eu rien que pour sa production un impact écologique identique à celui d’une voiture à combustion en 8 ans d’utilisation ? nous n’avons pas encore de solution pour recycler les batterie, pas plus que les autres déchets électroniques que l’europe envoie allègrement peuplée les côtes notamment africaines. .

la pollution numérique, c’est son nom, est un nouveau fléau encore peu connu du grand public, est pourtant son impact écologique est phénoménal. heureusement, des chercheurs se penchent déjà sur la questions. parmi eux, sophie, chercheuse en physique des matériaux, se consacre à la réduction énergétique de ce qu’on nomme les supra-supercalculateurs, des ordinateurs puissance 10 000 qui font tourner les monde, de google à l’armée. sophie est dynamique et particulièrement brillante. .

ensemble on parle de créer son propre destin, du sexisme dans le domaine de la science mais également des biais culturels, de pollution numérique, de recyclage des déchets électronique ou encore d’écologie. bonne écoute !
.
.
.
.
.
.
. .
.
.
.
.
.

text:
/ perempuan butuh syariat islam, bukan ruu pks /
.
pengamat politik dan pemerhati perempuan, pratama julia sunjandari, menilai alasan tingginya angka kekerasan seksual di indonesia yang menjadi latar belakang legalisasi rancangan undang undang (ruu) penghapusan kekerasan seksual (pks) sungguh mengada-ada.
.
pasalnya, menurut pratma, bukan sekadar ada umbrella act lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai. perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya atau gerakan #metoo yang kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual.
.
pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, “pertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai ‘amanah’ beijing platform for action (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa ‘kontrol seksual’ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.”
.
kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagi qawwam (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah.
.
“menjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,” ungkapnya kepada mnews, rabu (30/1/2019).
.
.
——

.

text:
m a r r i a g e:  is not easy folks!  but i will say with confidence that so much about our marriage has changed.  y’all, i had to understand that working against my partner is only hurting future opportunities in every area of our life. 
__
when i lost the need to be right.. the need to prove my point, it was like magic! ✨
the truth is, my ego wasn’t helping us.  it was hurting us.  our pride, ego, communication and lack of understanding was crippling us from shining individually and as partners. 
__
love and loyalty without limits is the only way to build! 
__
#loyalty #partnership #partners #team #love #acceptance #appreciate #marriage

text:
kasus #agni bukan kasus kekerasan seksual pertama yang terjadi di kampus, dan tentu bukan kasus terakhir

mengapa kekerasan seksual sering terjadi di kampus universitas, dan dilakukan baik mahasiswa maupun dosen? apakah gerakan #metoo yang sudah sangat mengubah perilaku dan cara berpikir di negara lain bisa berhasil di indonesia juga? dan bagaimana kita bisa membantu menghilangkan kekerasan seksual di kampus?

@jakartafeminist discussion group (jfdg) dan yayasan pantau menyelenggarakan 'diskusi kekerasan seksual dan gerakan #metoo di kampus' sebagai bagian dari rangkaian pra-acara women's march jakarta pada sabtu, 9 februari 2019 pukul 9.30 s.d. 13.00 wib di ruang komunal (facebook), one pacific place, senayan

dimoderatori febriana firdaus (wartawan, jakarta), diskusi ini dihadiri pembicara
1. citra maudy (reporter, balairung press, universitas gadjah mada, yogyakarta)
2. evi mariani (editor, the jakarta post, jakarta)
3. saras dewi (dosen, universitas indonesia, depok)

selain itu, ada penyerahan oktovianus pogau award kepada citra dan thovan dari balairung press @bppmbalairung yogyakarta untuk keberanian dalam jurnalisme. selengkapnya ada di http://pantau.or.id/?/=d/789 
registrasi bisa dilakukan di formulir berikut. tempat terbatas!

http://bit.ly/metookampuswmj2019

see ya there!

text: here is what being a strong woman means to me: it means standing up for myself. it means that i am a fully-functioning human, one who is independent and able to do things for herself. it means that i have opinions and beliefs that i stand for, and that i do not settle for less. it doesn’t mean that i don’t ask for help. i do (often). asking for help doesn’t mean i’m weak, it means i’m able to acknowledge that i’m not a super woman, and that i’m going to need other people sometimes. being strong doesn’t mean that i close myself off from others and act like i’m better than them. (actually, i’m always striving to be better, live better, love better, which is about me rather than anyone else.) it doesn’t mean that i force my beliefs down other people’s throats, or judge them for how they think. it doesn’t mean that i’m ‘inevitably bitter or jaded’. in fact, a strong woman is a woman who loves herself and her world and is therefore positive, loving, and self-assured. to be a strong woman simply means that i am grounded and confident in who i am....#womanempowerment #zimbabwe #love #success #inspiration #positivevibes #metoo #womanpower #life #metoo #art #beauty #beautiful #feminist #feminism #inspirationalquotes #successfulwomen #motivation #slayqueen #blackgirlsrock #myblackisbeautiful #melaninpoppin #blackwomen #makeup #entrepreneur  #blackownedbusiness #fashionstyle #beautifulpeople  #bhfyp

(actually, i’m always striving to be better, live better, love better, which is about me rather than anyone else.) it doesn’t mean that i force my beliefs down other people’s throats, or judge them for how they think. it doesn’t mean that i’m ‘inevitably bitter or jaded’. in fact, a strong woman is a woman who loves herself and her world and is therefore positive, loving, and self-assured. to be a strong woman simply means that i am grounded and confident in who i am....#womanempowerment #zimbabwe #love #success #inspiration #positivevibes #metoo #womanpower #life #metoo #art #beauty #beautiful #feminist #feminism #inspirationalquotes #successfulwomen #motivation #slayqueen #blackgirlsrock #myblackisbeautiful #melaninpoppin #blackwomen #makeup #entrepreneur  #blackownedbusiness #fashionstyle #beautifulpeople  #bhfyp

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

truth 04
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
you all must be wondering what is actually happening in the society. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
in the last few days, a number of women have come out and have shared that they were harassed by the people we see as our idols. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
where some accused these women of coming out late, some even told they this is just a publicity stunt. most importantly, all those who we always respected, or shall i say, all those who portrayed the image of saviors all these years, have taken a step back and aren’t willing to talk about it. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
well, in between all this, i would like to take a moment and remind you that yes, we are living in a strange world right now, where everyone knows everything, but are hiding it for their personal gains. 
the truth is, we all have either faced it, or have made someone face it. the truth is, we all know that we are living in a world where bad has outnumbered the good. how about we accept it. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
and if you accept it, this means it’s time you train yourself to figure out these predators. because as @theoffensivelad well said, whatever’s happening, it isn’t acceptable. it’s not normal. #nahichaltahai

text:
last night while i was going back home, two men followed me on their bike. they passed rude comments, and made offensive voices. 
i was paranoid! i was angry about the fact that even after all these campaigns, confessions, allegations and awareness, there are people who just don’t stop! i questioned myself why are we doing all this, if it is not changing anything?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
that is when i realised that when they were doing it all, i had the guts to take out my phone and make a video of their rude behaviour.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
that is when i realised that all these campaigns and struggles may not change others, but yes, they have a given me and many others the strength to fight and react to it. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
the truth is, yes, some people may never change and this may never stop. but better truth is, we won’t be oppressed by it now. we will act.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
till now we have been looking for heroes. but little did we know we are becoming one. ☺️

i was paranoid! i was angry about the fact that even after all these campaigns, confessions, allegations and awareness, there are people who just don’t stop! i questioned myself why are we doing all this, if it is not changing anything?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
that is when i realised that when they were doing it all, i had the guts to take out my phone and make a video of their rude behaviour.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
that is when i realised that all these campaigns and struggles may not change others, but yes, they have a given me and many others the strength to fight and react to it. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
the truth is, yes, some people may never change and this may never stop. but better truth is, we won’t be oppressed by it now. we will act.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
till now we have been looking for heroes. but little did we know we are becoming one. ☺️

“first of all, it’s about facing up to the problem,” said farfetch’s chief strategy officer and chair of the british fashion council, stephanie phair, on how #fashion can better embrace gender #diversity within the workplace. at last night’s #bofcareers community event, phair and bof’s imran amed addressed some of the specific challenges women face working in the fashion industry — an issue that has gained increasing momentum as the global #metoo movement spotlighted sexual misconduct within the creative industries and sparked industry-wide conversation on the continuing gender imbalance in the fashion industry.

text:
"we spend our lives drifting between glimpses of our own infinite glory and the fear that we suck." jen sincero #youareabadass

yes, we all have our insecurities...i hate it when mine show up acting like a old friend knocking at my door, so happy to see me. 🙄
luckily i hadn't seen that friend in s long, long time ...until last night. insecurity...go away!!😜 insecurities come from within and require some deep work on issues that we hide from the outside world.

this morning i am accepting the fact that i felt small, not important and insecure in a brief moment last night.....it didn't last long, but long enough to bring up old memories and things i just soon leave hidden.
it hurts...i feel shameful and then i get mad at myself for even feeling this way...it's like a big merry go round and i can't get off it!! ohh boyyy... i shall move forward with my day today and remember the things that i am so grateful for...😊🌸🐝🦋❤️
i will be gentle with myself and practice self love today....i will wipe away my insecurities with action, love and understanding.

have a fantastic day !!....
and i never forget...we are loved!!❤️😘 this too is part of growth....sigh...lol!...😝😌🤩
#insecure #selflove #metoo

text:
setelah kasus kekerasan seksual yang dialami seorang mahasiswi bernama agni di ugm diekspos oleh pers mahasiswa setempat, balairung press, ada peledakan pembahasan tentang kekerasan seksual di kampus universitas di seluruh indonesia. tetapi kasus agni bukan kasus kekerasan seksual pertama yang terjadi di kampus, dan tentu bukan kasus terakhir. sayang sekali, banyak korban belum pernah mendapatkan keadilan dan malah diremehkan, dirundung, diintimidasi, dan dikeluarkan universitas.
mengapa kekerasan seksual sering terjadi di kampus universitas, dan dilakukan baik mahasiswa maupun dosen? apakah gerakan #metoo yang sudah sangat mengubah perilaku dan cara berpikir di negara lain bisa berhasil di indonesia juga? dan bagaimana kita bisa membantu menghilangkan kekerasan seksual di kampus?

jakarta feminist discussion group (jfdg) dan yayasan pantau menyelenggarakan 'diskusi kekerasan seksual dan gerakan #metoo di kampus' sebagai bagian dari rangkaian pra-acara women's march jakarta pada sabtu, 9 februari 2019 pukul 9.30 s.d. 13.00 wib di ruang komunal (facebook), one pacific place, senayan.

dimoderatori febriana firdaus (wartawan, jakarta), diskusi ini dihadiri pembicara
1. citra maudy (editor, balairung press, universitas gadjah mada, yogyakarta)
2. evi mariani (editor, the jakarta post, jakarta)
3. saras dewi (dosen, universitas indonesia, depok)

registrasi bisa dilakukan di formulir berikut. tempat terbatas!

http://bit.ly/metookampuswmj2019

#bastraindo #womensmarchjkt #beranibersuara #metoo #hearmetoo #akujuga @dearcatcallers.id

text:
in 2014, steve bannon – then executive chairman of the “alt-right” news network breitbart – was christopher wylie’s boss. and robert mercer, the secretive us hedge-fund billionaire and republican donor, was cambridge analytica’s investor. and the idea they bought into was to bring big data and social media to an established military methodology – “information operations” – then turn it on the us electorate.

cambridge analytica’s parent company, scl, had won contracts with the us state department and was pitching to the pentagon, and wylie was genuinely freaked out. - it’s insane, he told me one night. - the company has created psychological profiles of 230 million americans. and now they want to work with the pentagon? it’s like nixon on steroids.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

david daniels — the international opera singer and professor at the university of michigan –together with his husband scott walters, were charged with sexual assault on tuesday night in the university town of ann arbor.

both are held at the washtenaw county michigan jail where they are waiting for extradition to texas where they will face the court for allegedly raping singer samuel schultz nearly ten years ago.

text:
i'm looking through the webshop where i buy all the books for work and saw that this little gem has been translated into english!! 😍
marta breen and jenny jordahl (illustrator) are very famous in norway for their feminist books, they've written loads. i really hope the rest of them are translated into english!
💎
so if you want a colorful, comic style, fast paced run-through of the battle women has been going through the last 150 years to today, this is it!
💎
ps : last year jenny jordahl wrote a children's picture book about a mermaid and a wood nymph that falls in love 😍 it's the first children's book with a gay couple i've ever read, and it was the cutest!
💎
maybe i should make a new hashtag #martinesnorwegianliteraturerecs 🤔
💎
💎
💎

text:
a few years back i would never have the courage to post a video like that. i’m a perfectionist, how could i post a video of me singing if i’m not a professional?! i am not and probably never will be a singer but this was such a special moment for me✨
。
on 30.12.2018 me and my boyfriend went out of the opera in leipzig after saying a musical goodbye to the old year⭐️
。
prior to that as a christmas gift for me my @fabianhochheimer learned how to play ‚shallow’ from ｌａｄｙ  ｇａｇａ 
and ｂｒａｄｌｅｙ  ｃｏｏｐｅｒ
and told me we need to sing it together in 2019😍
。
i haven’t practiced it but after the concert i got so inspired that i decided to sing
ｓｈａｌｌｏｗ 
in the opera house’s parking lot☺️
。
i am perfect in my imperfections.
this moment was magical✨
i love my boyfriend from this planet to the moon🌍💫🌕
。
。
。
fyi his car key was my microphone😂🗝💫🎤😎
。
。
。
and to paraphrase @ladygaga :
if there are 100 people in the room and i’m coming in there as 101st, there has to be only one person believing in me there -
ｍｅ.
the 100 will be surprised in some time🕊 talent, truth and love will always prevail✨☺️❤️
。
。
。
@starisbornmovie @gagavegas 💗💗💗
what do you think?🧿💎💫
。
#100peopleintheroom #100people #astarisborn #firsttime #goldenglobes #oscars #oscarforladygaga #talent #truth #love #perfection #imperfections #art #music #musicishealing #shallowcover #singing #wearefarfromtheshallownow #iamoffthedeepend #bradleycooper #cover #instagram #ladygaga #muterkelly #stopthehate #stopbullying #foreigner #metoo #stopprzemocy ✨
。
#justonething @priyankachopra i do it for you - i am enjoying every moment💛🧡❤️

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
but wylie wasn’t just talking about fashion. he had recently been exposed to a new discipline: “information operations”, which ranks alongside land, sea, air and space in the us military’s doctrine of the “five-dimensional battle space”. his brief ranged across the scl group – the british government has paid scl to conduct counter-extremism operations in the middle east, and the us department of defense has contracted it to work in afghanistan.

i tell him that another former employee described the firm as “mi6 for hire”, and i’d never quite understood it.
.
- it’s like dirty mi6 because you’re not constrained. there’s no having to go to a judge to apply for permission. it’s normal for a ‘market research company’ to amass data on domestic populations. and if you’re working in some country and there’s an auxiliary benefit to a current client with aligned interests, well that’s just a bonus.
.
when i ask how bannon even found scl, wylie tells me what sounds like a tall tale, though it’s one he can back up with an email about how mark block, a veteran republican strategist, happened to sit next to a cyberwarfare expert for the us air force on a plane. - and the cyberwarfare guy is like, ‘oh, you should meet scl. they do cyberwarfare for elections.’
.
it was bannon who took this idea to the mercers: robert mercer – the co-ceo of the hedge fund renaissance technologies, who used his billions to pursue a rightwing agenda, donating to republican causes and supporting republican candidates – and his daughter rebekah.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
how common are false allegations of rape or sexual assault?

one commonly cited figure holds that 5 percent of rape allegations are found to be false, but that figure paints a very incomplete picture, says belknap. typically, this figure comes from studies done on college students, an estimated 95 percent of whom do not report their assaults to police. overall, an estimated 8 to 10 percent of women are thought to report their rapes to the police, which means that — at the very highest — we can infer that 90 percent of rapes go unreported, says belknap. obviously, only those rapes that are reported in the first place can be considered falsely reported, so that 5 percent figure only applies to 10 percent (at most) of rapes that occur. this puts the actual false allegation figure closer to 0.5 percent.

text:
throughout the committee hearing, several republican senators including ted cruz and thom tillis pointed to the obama campaign’s use of facebook data, to highlight the fact that such practices are bipartisan.

however, people who downloaded the obama campaign app were aware they were using a political app. by contrast, the data obtained by cambridge analytica was obtained via a personality quiz application whose users had no idea their data would be used by a political campaign.

cambridge analytica improperly obtained the personal information of millions of facebook users to build profiles of us voters in order to target them with personalised political advertisements, via a related uk-based entity called scl elections.
.
- we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people’s profiles, said wylie in march. - and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.

wylie has previously told mps at a british select committee that the eu referendum was won through fraud after vote leave allegedly used a network of companies to get round election spending laws. he said he thought there “could have been a different outcome had there not been, in my view, cheating”. he also met privately with house democrats in april, but wednesday’s hearing was his first public appearance before us lawmakers.

olivia solon
the guardian

text:
#bellletstalk 💙
mental health has always been something i have struggled with for a large majority of my life. .
.
i finally found healing in sharing my story and i feel like i’m finally at a place where i feel open enough to share it with you. and i hope my story inspires you to keep moving forward. .
.
trigger warning ⚠️ ⚠️ ❌❌
.
.
7 years ago i was raped, and i spent the past few years distracting myself by pushing my emotions down, pretending like that part of my life did not exist. i was ashamed, i was scared, i felt disgusted with myself. i became cold, i pushed people away, and i developed terrible trust issues.
.
.
my buried emotions manifested into anger, anxiety, isolation, suicidal thoughts, and insomnia. i would use the gym, school, work, business, success, money and even other people’s problems, to distract myself from my own mind. .
.
after that event it was really difficult for me to love myself, and at times i still feel that way. i spent the last few years pulling away from my friendships, and relationships so i could focus on myself. heal myself, and love myself again. .
.
i had to reprogram my mind, my thoughts, and my beliefs about men. i had to learn how to forgive myself and let go of the past. i had to learn how to open my heart up to people who genuinely wanted to love  me. ❤️
.
.
letting go of trauma is not easy, it takes time and consistent effort. if you ever feel like giving up please let this be a reminder that there is life after trauma and there are people in your life that love you. .
.
to be completely honest there is anxiety that is filling up in my body as i write this message to you all and  my brain is doing whatever it takes to stop me but my heart is telling me that there is at least one other woman or man who has experienced the same experience i have....this message is for you, i love you. ❤️ #bellletstalk #endthestigma #mentalhealthawareness #metoo #trauma #love #depression #anxiety

text: enkelbiljett till #tokyo, #kyoto, #uji, #nara, #arashyama, #osaka, #himeji och #hiroshima. med lätt ryggsäck, noll planer och en brinnande passion för att vara någon annanstans hinner man rätt mycket. 🎲 slide 1: relativa ruiner. en märklig känsla att se den nakna nödtrappan alldeles förvriden och samtidigt veta att alla i byggnaden (160 m från hypocenter!) dog innan de ens kunde komma på tanken att använda trappan. 🥁2: oroande statistik som visar ett stort gap mellan andelen japaner och amerikaner som anser bombningen av hiroshima vara rättfärdigad. 🌍3: rörande teckningar. önskar att alla fick se dem. 🤑4: några meter under a-bombsruinerna har någon satt upp en skönhetsklinik i #metoo:s namn. känns också märkligt. 🤔5: förklarade noggrant, på japanska, att jag ville beställa #matcha utan mjölk. fick melonläsk toppad med mjukglass. 👹6: ville gå på nattklubb, fick rabatt, kunde inte vända om... 👀7: man vet inte vad det innebär att trängas förrän man har upplevt en nattklubb med sju våningar och en hiss i #shibuya. tänk de värsta ryktena om tokyos tunnelbana under rusningstimman, och diskokula ovanpå det. ❤️8: gåvan från den överjordiskt snälla personen som ordnade med biljett till western unions kontor när mitt bankkort utsatts för regionspärr. därmed kunde jag efter nio törstiga timmar på naritas flygplats äntligen komma vidare. tack gode gu...domliga människa! 😍9: taket i #asakusa! ❌10: svastikor ses inte som särskilt problematiska här. mjaehum... //. utan ryggsäck är man naken, sa pappa när jag var liten och skulle ut på min första tågluffning. japp, tänkte jag och packade ryggsäcken full med kapsyler. sen dess har jag lärt mig en del. 🎡

text:
​​#историичитателей

здравствуйте дорогие читатели, страницы «не молчи». я не давно открыл для себя вашу страницу, уже третий день читаю ваши посты и вдохновляюсь, переживаю, удивляюсь, сожалею.  мне захотелось рассказать вам свою историю, не знаю, наверное, будет много оскорблений... я самый младший ребёнок в семье, у меня одни братья, нет сестёр. я высокий, среднего телосложения, в детстве был похож на девчонку, беленький. 
родители  часто оставляли меня с моим братом, разница в возрасте у нас 6 лет. брат меня в детстве насиловал, но я боялся говорить об этом родителям в силу своего возраста. это продолжалось долгое время, пока мне не исполнилось 16 лет. 
я начал к этому привыкать, теперь меня интересуют парни. мне сейчас 23 и сложно жить с этим. я в этом не виноват, родители каждый день спрашивают об одном, когда свадьба, когда свадьба.

я пару раз с друзьями ходил к девчонкам, но у меня ничего не получилось с ними. влечения нет, может это травма? я не знаю, помогите мне... ================
из писем в @nemolchi.uz. вы можете отправить свою историю анонимно: https://goo.gl/forms/3nvmqxaflb5dq5b92 
внимание: под личными историями запрещены оскорбительные, обесценивающие и унижающие автора комментарии. если вы случайно оставили такой комментарий, пожалуйста, удалите его. в противном случае мы удалим его вместе с вами, не вступая в новые дискуссии.

"i guess that means he loves me right?" - an estimated 72% of females who commit suicide have experienced sexual or domestic abuse. the reason why people become suicidal are different, but abuse is a common denominator. if we want to see our suicide statistics change, we have to start by changing the things leading to it. 
full video premiering on facebook in 3 minutes! come and watch as we continue to remind our kids, teenagers and adults that abuse doesn't equal love. 
there is always hope.

text: it’s about damn time. last fall i took off the gloves and wrote a letter to the second senior in command of my aggressor after the senior in command, a captain, ruled “verbal counseling” was adequate accountability for the man who sexually assaulted me 🙄 when my lawyer and i asked the captain outright if he didn’t find me credible (remember that i have a written apology for what happened), the captain gave an excuse that was a lie and we allllll knew it. he was just hoping we’d let it go. protect the good ol’ boys club. 🙄🙄 once again, mama didn’t raise no quitter. my letter was finally reviewed and you know what, the admiral agreed with me. i have been pushing a boulder uphill for a year and a half and it’s finally at the top. there’s no where else for me to push it and it is finished. long ago i was able to separate my closure and healing from any “justice” but shoot it feels good. no idea what administrative action is, but it will leave a paper trail and it will follow him. hats off to the man who finally did the right thing, not just the easy thing. so much more to say but for now, it’s all 🙌🏼👊🏼👍🏼✊🏼 #sexualassault #metoo #metoomovement #aboutdamntime #justice #uphillbattle #sexualassaultawareness #itisfinished

text:
december 8, 2018 was the happiest & scariest  day of my life. many of you may ask, why? it should be the best day of your life? i too thought so. during my wedding planning i noticed that i was having frequent severe panic attacks, insomnia, hospital visits, paranoia, & negative suicide thoughts. my symptoms were manifesting worse & worse everyday. i kept asking myself, i love armand, why is all this happening? it’s as if my mind was telling me no, but my heart was telling me yes. i followed through with what my heart was telling me. i married him & i was the happiest girl once we said i do. 
after our picture taking, my anxiety, filled my heart w/ full blown panic & it just hit me out of nowhere. i looked at my sister, as if i made the biggest mistake of my life. i knew that moment there’s something wrong with me. i couldn’t chill & i couldn’t breathe. at my reception, i was in complete panic although i did not show that i was in terror. looking around at everyone, people congratulating me, & feeling as if all this was too overwhelming. i wanted to run away. i woke up the next day looking at armand in fear & left crying! we’ve been together for almost a decade, how is this possible?! i couldn’t even enjoy the intimacy the night of. 
my friends & family, i’ve been seeing a therapist & doctors and i am coming out of the closet. i have been educated that wedding stress had triggered a trauma response and am manifesting symptoms of c-ptsd (complex post traumatic stress disorder) due to *severe childhood trauma & abuse.
although this is a devastating time in my life as “a newly wed”, i see it as a blessing in disguise because i am now coming out to the world wanting to share my story & wanting to inspire others who have been affected by abuse. not only that, but to encourage women out there to never take shit from anyone. know your worth & fully love yourself first before you can love another person. there is happiness when you’re in a dark place & you have to fight for it. as i am now fighting so hard for my happiness and for my faith. through therapy & through god’s hands. this is our journey. this is my story. this is my recovery. #thebaclays #ptsd #cptsd #metoo

text:
i met armand in 2009. we met at cpk for a friend’s birthday. we shook hands & took it as nothing. we definitely connected on a genuine level for the first few days of hanging out while he was in town though. i instantly felt i could trust this person. luckily he wanted to get coffee & i took the opportunity to spend time. it could be a sign of support since i never really spoke about my past life. it was to the point where i felt hopeless & lost. my feelings and secrets was such a burden. i just wanted to feel happy. maybe talking about it to someone else could help heal my broken heart. i was in a dark place. 
i told him my life story and who i was at 18 years old. at the time he was 23. he didn’t judge me. he actually was concerned and asked me many things about abuse & what it’s like. i told him it felt normal but it no longer happens but i carried it forever without being able to fully express who i am or who i was. i was misunderstood by a lot of people and it sucked. he told me, it’s okay & i won’t ever tell your secrets. i accept you for who you are and we can continue to be friends if i ever needed someone to talk to. i felt gratified that i could share my life with someone who doesn’t think it’s “weird”.
the day he left, i remember when we said bye. i hugged him and at that moment i felt instant connection that i couldn’t explain. as if he was my soul mate. i kid you not. i didn’t even have feelings for him. never even thought of it once.  we let go & thought to myself, “woah that was something”. and once he left to go back to the bay, i felt lonely again more than ever. 
9 years later, i’m 27 now, he’s 33, we’re married. crazy to say, i am still in a dark place. time is repeating itself because i never really recovered. only to realize that i was in denial. though i feel empty, i know i am thankful that you are now my husband & i have a second chance. | #thebaclays #chooseme #metoo #childhoodtrauma #ptsd #cptsd #iwantitbaclay

text: post traumatic stress disorder (ptsd) has been one of the most difficult things that i have ever encountered in my entire life. it’s worse than the past literal moments of living through it because today, i am reliving it mentally & emotionally. sadly, it’s not even my fault. there are better days & there are dark days. i want to wish you all a happy new year & hope that 2019 brings you all joy because with pain & suffering, no one deserves it. only those who know what i am talking about can only relate to me & know i am with you guys. my new years resolution is self love & to inspire. love for myself and inspiration for healing through all the trauma i have gone through as a child. also to let others know it’s possible to heal from all the pain you kept in secret. i want to over come this mental illness, get back on track, and be the best me that i didn’t even know “she” existed. happy new year. let’s heal survivors! 💛🤲🏻 #ptsd #survivor #thebaclays #metoo #chooseme #childhoodtrauma #trauma

text:
throughout the committee hearing, several republican senators including ted cruz and thom tillis pointed to the obama campaign’s use of facebook data, to highlight the fact that such practices are bipartisan.

however, people who downloaded the obama campaign app were aware they were using a political app. by contrast, the data obtained by cambridge analytica was obtained via a personality quiz application whose users had no idea their data would be used by a political campaign.

cambridge analytica improperly obtained the personal information of millions of facebook users to build profiles of us voters in order to target them with personalised political advertisements, via a related uk-based entity called scl elections.
.
- we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people’s profiles, said wylie in march. - and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.

wylie has previously told mps at a british select committee that the eu referendum was won through fraud after vote leave allegedly used a network of companies to get round election spending laws. he said he thought there “could have been a different outcome had there not been, in my view, cheating”. he also met privately with house democrats in april, but wednesday’s hearing was his first public appearance before us lawmakers.

olivia solon
the guardian

text: i have depression. i have struggled with ptsd most of my life. i have attempted suicide, multiple times. i have been sexually abused as a child. i have battled with thinking i didn’t deserve to be a mother or wife or  live another day. i have been healed and torn open again and again. i have battled post pardum depression and been too ashamed to say so. i have lost many friends who haven’t wanted to “put up” with me. i have felt ostracized and ridiculed and looked at with judgment. i have almost lost my marriage, twice. i have battled chronic debilitating pain. i have made some really bad decisions. all while people onlook and say “but you look (this way) or you have (that)” or “how could you do that!?” no one knows the battles we face, the struggles we have endured or the sleepless nights or the fights in our mind. i have prayed in faith, asked for healing, prayed and fasted, taken every holistic recommendation, tried oils and diets etc, and i have taken western medication and given in to “big pharma”. i lay it all out there because ... this is my story, this is part of who i am. and i believe thru all the deep valleys and struggles god has a purpose and greater plan for these stories that don’t define me but have brought me to where i am. i see now the deep need for empathy. because nothing has helped as much as the love and true friendship i have experienced from a select people and my heavenly father  who have seen me and been there for me thru such darkness. thru fire we forge strength and endurance, so we are complete lacking nothing. god is full of grace & 🙏🏼loving-kindness and i say with full confidence he is there in our darkest moments when we come face to face with him and we are met with gentle, peaceful... love. that he will always meet you where you are, even if that’s with nothing face down confused on the floor in snot and tears or feeling fearless with your hair blowing in the wind. he is there, and those that truly know him will be there for you also. i know for damn sure i will know how to be there for my sister, my friend, a stranger, a neighbor because i too know, that life is not perfect and neither are we... and we all just need some love.
