a #virginia #democrat has proposed a 40-week #abortion bill – which would allow a woman to have an abortion all the way up until delivery. video of the politician explaining her bill quickly went viral.

in the footage, virginia house majority leader #toddgilbert (r) questioned delegate #kathytran (d) about her legislation.

gilbert: “where it’s obvious that a woman is about to give birth … she has physical signs that she is about to give birth would that still be a point at which she could request an abortion if she was so certified? if she’s dilating?” tran: “mr. chairman, that would be a decision that the doctor, the physician, and the woman would make at that point.” gilbert: “i understand that. i’m asking if your bill allows that.” tran: “my bill would allow that, yes.” #virginiagovernor also showed support for the bill. repost @dailyhourly

text:
throughout the committee hearing, several republican senators including ted cruz and thom tillis pointed to the obama campaign’s use of facebook data, to highlight the fact that such practices are bipartisan.

however, people who downloaded the obama campaign app were aware they were using a political app. by contrast, the data obtained by cambridge analytica was obtained via a personality quiz application whose users had no idea their data would be used by a political campaign.

cambridge analytica improperly obtained the personal information of millions of facebook users to build profiles of us voters in order to target them with personalised political advertisements, via a related uk-based entity called scl elections.
.
- we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people’s profiles, said wylie in march. - and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.

wylie has previously told mps at a british select committee that the eu referendum was won through fraud after vote leave allegedly used a network of companies to get round election spending laws. he said he thought there “could have been a different outcome had there not been, in my view, cheating”. he also met privately with house democrats in april, but wednesday’s hearing was his first public appearance before us lawmakers.

olivia solon
the guardian

text:
a boy i once cared for told me that his friend got him piss-drunk and sexually assaulted him. the friend pretended like it never happened the next day.
my friend told her mom that her step-dad had touched her inappropriately. her mom promised it would never happen again. but it did. 
my mother told me that when she used to walk to school as a child, a teenage boy would follow her and flash her. she told my grandma, but grandma told her that these kinds of things happen to everyone. 
well, apparently she was right. the first time it happened to me, i was seven years old. the second time - sixteen. i knew that no matter who i told, it wouldn’t matter. whatever i said would be brushed off. but i hoped- hoped so so badly- that someone would stand up for me or support me. but when i did open up about my experience, my loved ones asked me why i didn’t throw a fist at his face. they asked me why i didn’t run as far as my feet could carry me. and then, at the end of it all, they told me it was best that i forget what happened. 
at first, i told myself that what they said came from a place of love. i still don’t question that. but i don’t understand why the victims have to stay silent while the perpetrators sleep peacefully at night. why do the #survivors have to be triggered by the wrong word or touch while the abusers get to lead their lives unbothered? 
we need to change this. 
we have to change this. 
instead of teaching our loved ones to be quiet, we need to support them until they’ve gained the courage to break their silence and seek help.
so let my brothers and sisters speak their minds. let them not be ashamed of something they were not in control of. let them be the lotus flower that is born from the muck, that grows in the water and rises above it, unsoiled. 
#metoo

text:
"empowered women empower women"
///
oh wow, i didn't know that, just like when i thought women were fighting for similar rights just like men but now it has turned into only fighting for rights for the specifically. i don't know what happened, but things have been twisted and it just isn't about men, it isn't about "empowering" both of the sexes, it's about empowering them and they expect men to empower them because of their toxic dead brained mind to understand how egotistical that are & the arrogance that's flowing their actions and words. . . .
///
"triggered sexist men have arrived" 
yeah, they'll come because that's tired of exclusion and departure of them being thrown  under the rug because of your detrimental ideology that is only in support of women & how you degrade men's mentality, actions, and anything you can find about them to make them feel bad. and guess what, when you're fighting for your rights, and stepping all over people who are just trying to be them, the damage will already be done. there's no going back because you've already trampled on others for the things you want to achieve desperately; but in the wrong way.
///
"men don't need empowerment"
yeah, they do. you're just to stubborn and self absorbed in closure of your closed mindedness. you're only giving men/boys more and more reasons to leave and "walkway" from your misconceptions & dellusionary ideologies. no one's gonna be apart of that. and i don't support abusive and descriptively or verbal messages to be sent to others, i don't approve of that. but i don't approve of how this women's march has been doing. it's hateful, and i strongly disdain it.

text:
the 10th submission to the survivor tree project was perhaps the most difficult i’ve worked on so far. you can see my anxiety manifesting in the leaf itself, if you look carefully: my hand shook as i transcribed this woman’s powerful words. i had to stop and start several times, and the lines of cursive slipped and sloped as i lost myself in her story. •
i pored over this submission for a myriad of reasons. 1. the survivor who submitted it is one of the most important people in my life. lee and i bonded as soon as we met in the summer of 2014; and since then, she has occupied a special place within me. the day she submitted her story was the day i started wondering if i could do her words any sort of justice. 2. because, of all the stories i have transcribed thus far, this one is the most similar to what i went through 13 months ago. it’s still fresh. i still dream about it. i have always known that she and i are sisters in survivorship, but knowing that her experience echoed and emulated my nightmares so very closely left me feeling… raw. powerless. depleted. i wept as though i’d never stop because i felt like i knew her pain exactly as i know my own, and i didn’t want that for her. •
but the tears dried. i wiped my eyes, cleared my head, and transcribed her story. she is a warrior. she is an angel. i truly don’t know where i’d be without her. and she has not only helped me through her friendship: she has given herself to healing. she is the founder of survivor series- a community of survivors dedicated to encouraging and empowering the silenced. i was honored to be featured, and it was an amazing experience and significant step in my healing journey. one post is not enough to capture her story or her spirit or her strength, so i’ll let her work speak for itself: check out @seenheardbelieved and click the bio link. she has helped so many. she is moving mountains. she is transforming surviving into thriving. ✨🌱 click the link in my bio if others would like to contribute their story to #thesurvivortreeproject. #survivor #survivoradvocate #believesurvivors #believewomen #believeblackwomen #rapesurvivor #metoo #timesup #endrapeculture #metoomovement #artist

text:
pacific palisades
. 
marlon’s hand rested in mine on my lap. we rode the the 10 from downtown until it ended in santa monica. it had been six hours since i’d met him at his front door, four hours since dinner, two hours since i’d decided i was going to kiss him. i let go of him when i saw the road flares ahead, and moved to two-and-ten. we drove past a motorcycle on its side, then the loose shattered quarter panel of a car. a highway patrolman waved us by as his partner flashed a light in the drivers’ eyes. there was no rider in sight - but also no white sheet or ambulance. i turned up the music on the radio.
. 
we stopped at the end of mt. holyoke, as close as we could get to the small park at the edge of the bluff, and walked past a sign that listed the park hours, sunrise to sunset, but neither of us gave it more than a glance. this wasn’t young, cover-of darkness, reckless love. now, it’s after three in the morning, and the moon, well the moon is there, too. a quick online search reveals that on february 28, 2016, the moon was waning gibbous. perhaps, like a lighthouse, it’s a welcome on our arrival. perhaps, like a lighthouse, it’s a warning that can be heeded only in retrospect - too late. . 
out in the cold winter pacific breeze, or maybe because of the accident, he’s shivering. “want my sweater?” it’s not a question. not for the hundredth time but maybe thousandth time tonight, i smile, this time on seeing what he looks like in my clothes. when i wear that sweater now, it’s our “first date sweater.”
. 
we’ve talked about what he’s studying in grad school. his mom who’s a live-in caretaker. his sister who’s a voracious reader. his best friends who have no idea he’s on a date with a guy. . 
we’ve talked about the upcoming election and we don’t talk much about our fathers because there isn’t much to say - and that says plenty. . 
i’ve told him that i’m the oldest of four, but second of five if you count my best friend, and i do, who is now a brother to me. i’ve told him about every single job i’ve had and my small run ins with the law. i’ve showed off by speaking in perfect spanish and french and portuguese. cont.

text:
•• r e c o v e r y •• the stages of recovery after trauma  #advocate #idaho ——————————————————————— every survivor’s journey to healing is different and shouldn’t be rushed.
for those who have lived through the trauma of an abusive or violent partner, they may expect an instant sense of relief once they’ve escaped, a calming peace after they shut the door on that chapter of their lives.
instead, what they can experience is sometimes completely different. instead of tranquility, they may feel inches. instead of joy, they may feel guilt.
or, they may feel nothing at all.
this, see therapists, is normal. they are emotions that come with the stages of recovery after trauma.
“trauma recovery looks different for everyone, “says relationship therapist amie piekarz, lsw. “sometimes, clients feel like there is something wrong with them, or that they are ‘failing’ at recovery because they read books and can’t relate to others have coped.”
here’s a look at what the three stages might look like:

text:
•• r e c u p e r a c i ó n •• las etapas de la recuperación después del trauma  #defensores #idaho ————————————————————————– el viaje de cada sobreviviente hacia la curación es diferente y no se debe apresurar.
para aquellos que han vivido el trauma de una pareja abusiva o violenta, pueden esperar una sensación instantánea de alivio una vez que hayan escapado, una paz calmada después de cerrar la puerta a ese capítulo de sus vidas.
en cambio, lo que se puede experimentar es a veces completamente diferente. en lugar de tranquilidad, pueden sentir ansiedad. en lugar de alegría, pueden sentirse culpables.
o bien, pueden sentir nada en absoluto.
esto, según los terapeutas, es normal. son emociones que vienen con las etapas de recuperación después del trauma.
"la recuperación del trauma se ve diferente para todos", dice la terapeuta de relaciones amie piekarz, lsw. "a veces, los clientes sienten que hay algo mal con ellos, o que están “fallando” en la recuperación porque leen libros y no se pueden relacionar con lo que otros han enfrentado".
tomemos un vistazo a cómo se verían las tres etapas:

text:
toxic masculinity: yes, its personal.

i have a lot to say about the viral conversation that's happening right now about #toxicmasculinity. like, a lot.

i've realized that while i have been writing about my own healing coming out of a toxic #karmicrelationship, it really boils down to a story about my relationship with the toxic masculine. it's a relationship that goes way back.

this really is a conversation about all of us, as adults, being able to step up and heal ourselves and our relationship to our spiritual power, over egoic power, so that we can pass along that understanding and presence to our children.

toxic masculinity is learned, it is not innate. and we have the ability to learn it young, if we are wounded early enough. which, sadly, most of us were.

i was only in elementary school when i was teased for being too "girly." i remember being bullied for being excited to learn about my body in biology class, excited and amazed by the fact that the female body is designed to create and birth life. like, wow, that is some serious spiritual power, and i wanted to know all about it.

but someone else had been wounded, they knew the mind of the toxic masculine, they lashed out at me, and it cut me deep. (i'm still healing from this one actually.) over the years, i'd experience more teasing, most of it directed at the more feminine traits i expressed. my passion, idealism, intuition, vision, creativity, sensitivity and empathy. all were fair game to attack.

what i've learned through my adult experience of serial relationships with toxic masculinity is that it is not relegated only to males, and it hurts everyone.

i've learned that at its core, this mentality has an energy of wanting to attack, break down, destroy, and suppress the feminine. what i understand is that this comes from a deep seated fear.

there's a fear that is the driving force behind the mentality of being unable to acknowledge or accept the feminine within, or in a form outside of self.

let me make this clear: i am not talking men vs women here. this is about the yin and yang elements of the energy of all life.

continued in comments... ⬇️

text:
1970 ... that means i’m 49. for real how did that happen and why is this my #midlifecrisis? i actually think i’m clocking in a second midlife crisis here. 
in a haze and whirl of too many parties and drugs wrapped in a great big blanket of #metoo i ran away from nc to start a new world in #seattle. i am now a multicolored hair aging #hipster on #capitolhill in seattle that had quite an amazing ride working for #microsoft for 5 years before a contract was yanked out from under me (promise a post on that later). that running away and starting a #newlife was a benchmark of some type of midlife crisis ... i’ve seen and heard other tales of people chucking their lives to the winds and heading for something new and different. i do not look back - nor do i regret!

now i’m in school at seattle central college #scc in web development. i love what i am studying but the stress of living a 20 year old existence in an almost 50 year old body can be intense af! 
but once again i am not alone. this is the newest level of midlife crisis for #genx. we don’t get fancy sports cars we get to go back to school. genx is right smack in the middle of aging and burgeoning technologies and we have to pay the price to learn the new stuff while defending the old stuff. hardly anyone cares about my #excel skills it’s more a case of “why don’t you know #sql already?” old school “keep to yourself and create your own” workspace has been replaced by #pairprograming and the age of #github and shared #repositories. in the #it world staying vital means staying up on the latest and greatest. with #genx we are still holding onto an expectation that life comes with one job you work until you get your #goldpocketwatch and the job cares about you and sponsors your development. that is not the case in the millennial marketplace. if you aren’t teaching yourself no one cares if you are left behind. some of us out there got that message sooner than others. if that message came through i didn’t get it. i get it now! 
although school is an epic struggle of finances and #packagedramen it is worth the struggle. i have to believe and have faith that it is.

text:
setelah kasus kekerasan seksual yang dialami seorang mahasiswi bernama agni di ugm diekspos oleh pers mahasiswa setempat, balairung press, ada peledakan pembahasan tentang kekerasan seksual di kampus universitas di seluruh indonesia. tetapi kasus agni bukan kasus kekerasan seksual pertama yang terjadi di kampus, dan tentu bukan kasus terakhir. sayang sekali, banyak korban belum pernah mendapatkan keadilan dan malah diremehkan, dirundung, diintimidasi, dan dikeluarkan universitas.
mengapa kekerasan seksual sering terjadi di kampus universitas, dan dilakukan baik mahasiswa maupun dosen? apakah gerakan #metoo yang sudah sangat mengubah perilaku dan cara berpikir di negara lain bisa berhasil di indonesia juga? dan bagaimana kita bisa membantu menghilangkan kekerasan seksual di kampus?

jakarta feminist discussion group (jfdg) dan yayasan pantau menyelenggarakan 'diskusi kekerasan seksual dan gerakan #metoo di kampus' sebagai bagian dari rangkaian pra-acara women's march jakarta pada sabtu, 9 februari 2019 pukul 9.30 s.d. 13.00 wib di ruang komunal (facebook), one pacific place, senayan.

dimoderatori febriana firdaus (wartawan, jakarta), diskusi ini dihadiri pembicara
1. citra maudy (editor, balairung press, universitas gadjah mada, yogyakarta)
2. evi mariani (editor, the jakarta post, jakarta)
3. saras dewi (dosen, universitas indonesia, depok)

registrasi bisa dilakukan di formulir berikut. tempat terbatas!

http://bit.ly/metookampuswmj2019

#womensmarchjkt #beranibersuara #metoo #hearmetoo #akujuga

info ke @womensmarchjkt dan @febrofirdaus

text:
about that...
the average woman menstruates for 40 yrs of her life and uses around 10,000 pads and tampons a year. every month women throw away thousands of disposable hygiene products and their toxic packaging. 
in the u.s. alone, women contribute 12 billion pads and 7 million tampons to landfills each year.
have you ever wondered why technology hasn’t advanced to a more eco-friendly alternative  for our bodies and our planet?
well, that’s the problem- technology has advanced just not in favor of the billion dollar disposable hygiene product industry. 
so it’s time to create our own change! 
in other words, cup it up buttercup! 🌸

text:
-content warning: sexual assault-
there are things that remain
i long to release 
but every time i stir them up in my mind
words refuse to exit my mouth 
if i allow my consciousness to descend 
into the cavern where those truths reside
stepping down each rung with a caution
a weightlessness i grew accustomed to
sacrificing my voice 
ensuring the darkness i hid in 
remained in tact
landmines buried to keep me in line 
you joked you’d never hit me
because i was bigger than you
the way you’d be certain to say with a smile
“i want to shake you”
“i left so i wouldn’t hit you”
as though i should be grateful 
for such restraint 
you never laid your hands on me 
at least not in the daylight 
not in the ways that one could point to
when nothing felt right 
your words beat me instead 
battered down
bloody 
cement poured down my throat
setting in my every joint
making it easier each time to ignore
my words
calling me a tease
when all i did was breathe
existing each moment
cautious with every movement so 
as to not unintentionally entice 
shut myself in that tiny bathroom
pieces of me falling off
sobbing in silence 
aching
bleeding 
while 20 feet away you rested peacefully 
are you even aware of what you did to me?
all this time later
i still can’t call it what it was

a piece of me still sits in that darkness
hidden away for fear of what those i 
love will say 
the day that shadow i left inside
breaks away 
aches too deeply for the light 
to stay left behind
—————————————————i have to admit, this isn’t the first poem i’ve written about this experience, but it is by far the most transparent, and posting it was not a decision that i took lightly. i  just want you to know that no matter what you are going through, you are never alone and you will get through this. i know there are days it doesn’t feel this way. seven months have passed and there are still days where i can’t see past it, but i will. 💖🦋 #photography #poetrycommunity #enlightenment #singersongwriter #singersofinstagram #photographer #metoo #lyrics

text:
my body is mine.
my choices for and about it may not be “right” to everyone
but the opinions of others is none of my business

i am a woman.
i am a good woman.
defined solely by her capacity for love and light in this world

i am a good woman with an ass tattoo that is here to tell you that a woman’s body is hers and she can do with it what she pleases, whether that is stay the same, change it, show it off, keep it covered... whatever

as long as she is doing it out of love

unconditional. love.

i have unconditional love for whatever the fuck it is a woman wants to do in this life and none of that requires hypersexualization, or judgment

so much of my mission on social media is to spread the word that my body.. your body.. any woman’s body is the vessel to her soul, not an exotic object

and any resistance that comes my way on that mission just reminds me how much i value unconditional love for and from everyone in this life

and to all the people in my life that love me without judgment or conditions....i love you to the moon and back (haha get it?🌙)
———
#feminism #nastywoman #smashthepatriarchy #metoo #unconditionallove #womensmovement #spreadlovenotjudgement #youdoyouboo #immadome

text:
update, 18.30 wib, 31 jan: kuota sudah penuh.  terima kasih atas ketertarikannya. nanti akan ada facebook live juga.

setelah kasus kekerasan seksual yang dialami seorang mahasiswi bernama agni di ugm diekspos oleh pers mahasiswa setempat, balairung press, ada peledakan pembahasan tentang kekerasan seksual di kampus universitas di seluruh indonesia.

tetapi kasus agni bukan kasus kekerasan seksual pertama yang terjadi di kampus, dan tentu bukan kasus terakhir. sayang sekali, banyak korban belum pernah mendapatkan keadilan dan malah diremehkan, dirundung, diintimidasi, dan dikeluarkan universitas.

mengapa kekerasan seksual sering terjadi di kampus universitas, dan dilakukan baik mahasiswa maupun dosen? apakah gerakan #metoo yang sudah sangat mengubah perilaku dan cara berpikir di negara lain bisa berhasil di indonesia juga? dan bagaimana kita bisa membantu menghilangkan kekerasan seksual di kampus?

jakarta feminist discussion group (jfdg) dan yayasan pantau menyelenggarakan 'diskusi kekerasan seksual dan gerakan #metoo di kampus' sebagai bagian dari rangkaian pra-acara women's march jakarta pada sabtu, 9 februari 2019 pukul 9.30 s.d. 13.00 wib di ruang komunal (facebook), one pacific place, senayan.

dimoderatori febriana firdaus (wartawan, jakarta), diskusi ini dihadiri pembicara
1. citra maudy (reporter, balairung press, universitas gadjah mada, yogyakarta)
2. evi mariani (editor, the jakarta post, jakarta)
3. saras dewi (dosen, universitas indonesia, depok)

sekalian ada ada penyerahan oktovianus pogau award kepada citra dan thovan dari balairung press @bppmbalairung yogyakarta untuk keberanian dalam jurnalisme. selengkapnya ada di http://pantau.or.id/?/=d/789 
registrasi bisa dilakukan di formulir berikut. tempat terbatas!

http://bit.ly/metookampuswmj2019

mengapa kekerasan seksual sering terjadi di kampus universitas, dan dilakukan baik mahasiswa maupun dosen? apakah gerakan #metoo yang sudah sangat mengubah perilaku dan cara berpikir di negara lain bisa berhasil di indonesia juga? dan bagaimana kita bisa membantu menghilangkan kekerasan seksual di kampus?

jakarta feminist discussion group (jfdg) dan yayasan pantau menyelenggarakan 'diskusi kekerasan seksual dan gerakan #metoo di kampus' sebagai bagian dari rangkaian pra-acara women's march jakarta pada sabtu, 9 februari 2019 pukul 9.30 s.d. 13.00 wib di ruang komunal (facebook), one pacific place, senayan.

2. evi mariani (editor, the jakarta post, jakarta)
3. saras dewi (dosen, universitas indonesia, depok)

text: last weekend i spoke to a room full of sexual assault survivors. i could see the scars on their hearts and heard the stories of their healing. some of that healing had only been introduced 5 minutes prior. there’s an idea about sexual assault that it only is valid if it was violent. many times it is, but sometimes it’s an ignored series of “no.” that is just as valid. if you or anyone you know has stayed silent because their lack of consent was ignored, that doesn’t make it okay. sexual assault is like a plague on college campuses and as i watched the latest episode of the bachelor my heart sank listening to @caelynnmillerkeyes talk about her very traumatic (& more violent than mine) experience. i have to publicly acknowledge her bravery here because this topic is something i’ll never stop fighting for and it was so empowering to hear her speak up. if you have been sexually assaulted and have been struggling with ptsd, please tell someone that is a safe person. we have resources at @unveiledcampaign for you online and i personally won’t stop fighting for us. if you want to raise awareness at your college on this topic, please reach out so i can join you in the war, on the ground.

text:
unfortunately this was a scene that was a norm in my home when i was married to my ex. i remember feeling on edge most of the time, never knowing what mood or state of mind he would be in. living on egg shells because his anger was always bubbling under the surface, and i never knew when he would explode.

gosh, living like that for years really messed with my head. the name calling, manipulation, control, gaslighting, emotional/mental/physical abuse, and isolation made my life fearful and miserable.

thank god i'm free from that life...emotionally, physically, spiritually and mentally free. it's taken years and hard work to detox myself from this shit. but worth it.

if the above pic is a "norm" in your relationship and/or home, please know it's not normal...took me years to realize this truth. know that abuse escalates and slowly gets worse. and that there is help, and life can be much better than what you may be experiencing.

to my fellow dv survivors, i know many of you can relate to what i'm 😊 saying. freedom feels good doesnt it?

still a queen 👑✊.
.
.
.

text:
#bellletstalk 👊🏼💙 for the days when i would cry endlessly because i felt like i couldn’t handle what life had placed in front of me, for all the times i couldn’t get out of bed because i felt like giving up, for the times i felt like my children needed ‘better’, and i was a terrible mom, or the times i avoided gatherings with friends because i just couldn’t bare having a room full of people “watching and judging” me. #bellletstalk 👊🏼💙 all those times i couldn’t breathe, and felt that horrible prickly heat all over my body that just wouldn’t stop, making me feel like i had something crawling over my body, or the times that i couldn’t bare my husband helping me because the black plates were stacked on the blue plates, and i panicked, or the countless times i felt rushed by the clock and couldn’t move faster than slow motion. 
lets talk. let’s end the stigma. on the outside, i look fairly ordinary. i have a career, two children, and a husband who loves me so much is sickening, i am generally healthy to the naked eye, have everything going for me.... except a brain that chooses to allow happiness, calm, disorganization, and patience. not everyone who looks like they are thriving with ease truly are. we all have skeletons in our closets. let them out, and #letstalk 🙏🏼
